title: beef, cabbage and noodles
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Drain all fat.
Add oil, soy sauce and water to beef mixture.
Add cabbage, sliced in thin wedges and ramen noodles broken up over mixture.
Add flavor packet from noodles, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, covered, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tracy's mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender and separate chicken from bones, tearing into small strips.
Crunch up Doritos into bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle 8 tablespoons chicken broth over the Doritos.
Layer strips of chicken over this and then layer Ro-Tel, then soups, then cheese over all.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: sherrie's brownie mousse
directions: Bake any brownie mix as directed.
Mix 2 envelopes Knorr milk chocolate mousse dessert mix as directed.
When brownies are cool, cut in 1/2.
Crumble 1/2 of brownies in the bottom of dish. Spread 1/2 of the mousse on brownie.
Layer a crushed Heath or Butterfinger candy bar on this.
Add a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Top with additional candy pieces.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat with a fork the eggs.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir just enough for flour to be moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Add 2 cups blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: chicken chili
directions: Heat oil and add onions and garlic powder.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until tender.
Add bite-size pieces of chicken, chili powder and cumin.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes until chicken loses raw color and is well coated with seasonings.
Add tomatoes, beans and corn.
Bring to a boil and simmer covered 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 to 10 minutes until chicken is cooked through and sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat and season with salt.
Sprinkle with parsley and grated cheese to serve.

title: magnolia chicken
directions: Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Add the flour and mix well.
Pour in the milk and stir continuously until thick.
Add the remaining ingredients except the bread crumbs and the egg. Mix well and chill for 30 minutes.
Coat each piece of chicken evenly with bread crumbs, dip in egg, and coat again in bread crumbs. Deep fry until golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line large pan with graham cracker crust.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat on low 20 minutes; pour into crust.

title: pancit guisado
directions: Boil shredded chicken or pork 15 minutes.
Saute garlic in 1/3 cup oil.
Add onion and fry.
Add chicken or pork and fry 5 minutes.
Add celery, carrots and beans; cook until tender.
Add remaining vegetables, soy sauce and Accent.
Cook until tender.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Wash berries and crush. Heat to a boil and squeeze out juice. To 3 1/2 cups of juice, add lemon juice.
Measure 4 1/2 cups sugar into a dry dish.
Pour juice into a large kettle.
Add pectin and stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Add measured sugar and mix well. Continue stirring and bring to a full rolling boil.
Pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: glenda's punch
directions: Freeze Kool-Aid until slushy.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in a small shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar and shake vigorously;	pour over asparagus. Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Yield: about 4 servings.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken in half and put in roaster.
Mix vinegar, catsup, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Cover roaster and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Take cover off and baste with juice. Keep basting until brown and tender.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, Crisco together.
Add water to form a ball. Roll out to make bottom crust.
Put in pie plate.

title: weitkunat's birthday cake(never fail chocolate cake)
directions: Place into large bowl in given order.
Do not mix until last item is in the bowl.
Beat for 3 to 5 minutes until all ingredients are blended well.
Grease pan, 11 x 17-inch (large).
Bake at 350° until done.
Will spring back when touched in center.

title: zucchini mandarin orange bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Mix all ingredients in order given; pour into pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tex mex skillet
directions: In a large skillet, add chili beans, tomato juice, rice and meat (sliced thick).
Cover, cook on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Top with grated cheese and taco chips.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables with mayonnaise, cheese and seasonings.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with butter; spread on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Boil until onion is done.
Turn heat down and let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
In medium bowl combine crumbs and butter.
Press on bottom of well-greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.
In small mixing bowl beat egg yolks; blend in cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Beat until smooth and light.
In separate bowl beat egg whites until stiff.
In separate bowl whip cream until stiff.
Fold egg whites and whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
Swirl half of raspberries into mixture.
Pour into crust.
Spoon remaining raspberries onto corners of pan; swirl.
Cover; freeze at last 1 hour.
Keep frozen.

title: meat filled manicotti
directions: Cook shells as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Brown ground beef with onion.
Cook and drain grease. Mix together, meat, and all remaining ingredients.
Stuff shells. Place in a single layer in a greased baking pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells with grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until hot.
May need to cook for 1 hour.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased, floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350` oven (325° for glass pan).

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix butter, flour and chopped pecans together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with cool oleo, saving some crumbs for top of dessert.
Put mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour on top of cookies.
Sprinkle with remaining Oreos.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: walnut date muffins
directions: Mix cereal
and milk in a medium sized bowl.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes, until milk is absorbed.
Preheat oven to 400°. Grease muffin cups or use paper liners.
Beat egg and oil with cereal. Stir
in dates, nuts and orange peel.
Mix dry ingredients in large
bowl.
Pour
in liquid ingredients.
Fold in with rubber spatula, just until dry ingredients are moistened. Scoop batter into
muffin
cups.
Bake
at
400° for 15 to 25 minutes or until spongy to touch in center.

title: jumbo pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; stir well and set aside. Combine pumpkin and next 3 ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add onion and egg.
Mix and beat well.
(If using self-rising cornmeal, omit baking powder.)
Add milk, a little at a time, until batter is smooth.

title: crock-pot squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, carrots and soup. Mix together sour cream and flour;
stir into vegetables. Toss stuffing mix with butter. Spread half in bottom of slow cooker. Add vegetable mixture. Top with remaining crumbs. Cover; cook on low 7 to 9 hours.

title: blueberry special
directions: Melt oleo and pour first four ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat next four ingredients until smooth.
Place over crust and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and let cool.
Spread with pie filling.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1 tablespoon for 1 cup boiling water or to taste.

title: fruity cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar and Jell-O.
Cream well after each addition.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing after each addition until smooth.
Roll and cut out or cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 13 or 15 minutes or until edges are brown.
Store in loosely covered container.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger with onion in pan until hamburger is done. Drain grease.
If making chicken enchiladas, bone chicken and shred.
Add onion to shredded chicken.
When hamburger or chicken is warm, but not hot, add cheeses.
Mix together until cheeses melt slightly.
Add minced garlic and salt to taste.

title: black cherry cobbler
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: chocolate trash
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter in heavy saucepan. In a large bowl, mix Rice Chex, peanuts and pecans. Pour chocolate mixture over this. Mix until chocolate coats all ingredients. Let stand until cool. Pour powdered sugar into garbage bag and then add mixture and shake well. Ready to serve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add chicken, onion and green pepper; cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Add corn, broth and salsa. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes; sprinkle with cheese until melts.

title: seafoam
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and cream
of tartar.
Cover and boil 5 minutes.
Uncover.
Wipe sides of saucepan with a damp cloth.
Boil without stirring to firm ball stage.
Pour slowly, beating constantly, over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add flavoring.
Continue beating until candy holds its shape when dropped from spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Sprinkle with rose-colored coconut.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add onion, beans, catsup and chili powder.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
If it is too dry, add 1/2 cup of water.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows: first layer is meat mixture, second layer is sour cream and third layer is cheese.
You make real thin layers.
Repeat one more time.
Add extra cheese on top.
Cover.
Place in oven at 325° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Take cover off.
Bake 5 more minutes. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: espresso cheese cake
directions: Mix graham
cracker crumbs, extract and butter, by hand and press onto	bottom	and
side
of
9-inch
spring-form pan (bring crust to within
an
inch
from top of pan). Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°
in
small saucepan over low heat, melt 6 squares semi-sweet	chocolate,
stirring frequently.
In large bowl with mixer at
low speed, beat cream cheese until smooth. Add melted chocolate,	eggs,
sugar and milk.	Dissolve coffee powder in 5 teaspoons
very hot water and add. Beat until well blended, beat 3 minutes.
Pour
cream
cheese mix into crust. Bake 45 minutes. Cool
cheese cake in pan.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Garnish with grated chocolate.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies until you have coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
To the rest, add the melted butter; mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cheese with electric mixer; add powdered sugar and beat well.
Fold in 1/2 whipped cream topping. Spread mixture on top of crust and chill for 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups milk, spread on top of cream cheese layer. Chill one hour.
Top with remaining whipped cream topping. Sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs 1 hour before serving.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken skin sides up in ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with salt, paprika and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Heat broth to boiling. Remove chicken and drain fat from dish.
Mix broth, rice, onion, garlic, oregano, bay leaf and peas in baking dish.
Top with chicken; cover with aluminum foil.
Cook in oven until rice and thickest pieces of chicken are done and liquid is absorbed, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with pimento strips and olives.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan cook and stir bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Stir in soup and milk, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Stir in clams, lemon juice and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Yields 4 servings at 1 cup each.

title: barbecue sauced potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4 inch thick.
Arrange potatoes and onion slices with smaller pieces toward center.
Stir water and barbecue sauce together and pour over.
Cook on high about 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix cheeses, eggs, seasonings and thawed spinach.
Put about 3/4 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put in one layer of noodles and 1/3 cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Keep layering until all ingredients are used.
Make sure you use generous amount of sauce between layers.
Pour 1/2 cup of water around edges of pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove foil and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with the salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place in Dutch oven with the butter, bacon and onion and brown roast on top of stove until all sides are brown.
Remove the onion and bacon pieces and add 1 cup water and the tomato sauce.
Cover roast and allow to cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, according to desired tenderness.
Remove roast from pan.
Make gravy by placing flour in cup and adding slowly enough water to fill cup, stirring until smooth.
Add slowly to broth already in pan and simmer until slightly thick.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Take pork chops; cut in cubes.
Take teaspoon of garlic salt and sprinkle on pork chops.
Cut bell pepper in cubes.
Cut onion in cubes.
Start rice and cook as directions call for.
Use large wok or skillet.
Take 1 tablespoon of butter and melt; add pork chops.
Brown and remove.
Add tablespoon of butter.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Take egg and add to skillet; scramble.
Add rice, pork chops and soy sauce.
Stir and serve.

title: cookie's homemade chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in large soup pot filled with water to cover chicken for 1 hour or until done along with 4 chicken bouillon. After cooked, remove from pot and place in colander in drainer to cool.
While chicken is draining, take the water left in pot and add rice, celery (chopped small) and onions (also diced) and cook until done, about 20 minutes.
Debone and skin chicken and add it to the rest; salt to taste.
Heat through and you have Cookie's Homemade Soup.

title: instant torte
directions: Mix flour and butter together like pie crust.
Add chopped nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: frosted creams
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° in a shallow pan for 20 minutes.
When cool, frost with a powdered sugar frosting.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24.

title: railroad cornbread pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in pan.
Add soup, water, salt, pepper, chili powder, green pepper and corn.
Mix this well and put into an ovenproof dish.
In another bowl, mix rest of ingredients.
Drop this mixture by spoonfuls onto the vegetable mixture in oven dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no fuss no mess chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in oblong pan.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups and water; pour over top of chicken and rice.
Bake uncovered 2 hours in 300° oven.

title: party mix
directions: Combine cereal and pretzels in large bowl.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan; mix in nuts and saute for 15 minutes.
Stir to coat evenly.
Add spices and mix well.
Add cereal and pretzels.
Stir until well coated.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Save part of onion rings for top of casserole.
Mix beans, soup and onion rings.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings and Parmesan cheese on top of casserole.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Split package of rolls lengthwise.
(There should be a top and bottom layer.)
Combine minced onion, poppy seed, garlic powder and butter.
Spread butter mixture on bottom layer of rolls. Layer cheese, ham and another layer of cheese.
Replace top layer of rolls.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
(You may want to cover rolls with foil after baking to keep soft.)

title: king of the hill texas minute steak
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray. Arrange your meat in a large skillet and add one cup water. Cook for 7 to 10 minutes and then add Rotel and mushroom soup. Add your spices and cook for 20 minutes or until the soup and rotel have made a rich sauce.

title: butter pecan turtle bars
directions: Mix together butter and brown sugar and cook over medium heat in heavy 1-quart saucepan, stirring constantly, until entire surface begins to boil.
Continue to boil 1/2 to 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour evenly over pecan layer.
Bake near center of 350° oven for 18 to 22 minutes until entire caramel layer is bubbly; remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips on caramel layer.
Allow to melt slightly for 2 to 3 minutes, then swirl slightly.
Don't spread, leave some whole for a marbled effect.

title: pat's reuben casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add sour cream. Cube the bread and add to the mixture. Coat well.
Pour half of bread mixture into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Layer half of the corned beef, then half the sauerkraut, cheese and olives. Repeat layers.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat soups and milk in large saucepan until well blended and warm.
Add half of butter and all of rice. Stir and remove from heat.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Pour rest of butter over this.
Bake,
uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in bottom of a 9 x 9 pan. Mix the flour, baking powder, salt, margarine, sugar and milk and pour over fruit.
Spread to cover.
Mix together the 1/2 c. sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle over cake.
Pour water over the top. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: fisherman's wharf
directions: Layer 1/2 of bread cubes, seafood, mushrooms and cheese. Repeat.
Beat eggs and milk with dry mustard, salt and pepper. Pour liquid over casserole and press firmly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frying pan; drain. Mix the catsup, mustard, brown sugar, onion and pork and beans with the ground beef. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine and rinse well with cold water.
Add all but the dressing and mix well.
Add Italian dressing and marinate at least 6 hours.
(Better overnight.)
Serves 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut in small pieces.
Place chicken in a casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken. Crush crackers and place over second layer.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: date fingers
directions: Cook sugar, butter and dates very slowly over low heat, stirring constantly, until dates are soft.
Pour hot mixture over (mixed) nuts and cereal. Stir well.
Roll small amount of mixture in palms of well buttered hands.
Make into fingers and roll in coconut.
Place on waxed paper to dry a few minutes.
Store in closed container, putting waxed paper between layers.
Keeps indefinitely.
Makes 60 to 70.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef and onion in butter until onion is tender and ground beef is cooked.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms; cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup; simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with sliced green apples, unpeeled.

title: scrumptious (or sin) pie
directions: Butter pan lightly.
Mix and press in pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Cool and chill thoroughly.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Wrap meat around potato. Top with onion, butter and cheese. Fold in aluminum foil and bake at 375° until potatoes are done.

title: dorito delight
directions: Brown ground meat and onions.
Add jalapeno peppers.
Mix both cans of soup and Pet milk; add to meat mixture.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan crumble enough chips to cover bottom of pan.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Line sides of pan with whole chips.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: cherry delights
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Stir in light corn syrup, egg yolks and flour.
Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into egg whites, then chopped nuts.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press candied halves into centers.
Bake in 325° oven 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oven french toast
directions: Melt margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon in bottom of 9 x 13-inch aluminum pan (not a glass pan).
Cover with 2 layers of bread.
Mix
eggs,	milk and salt.	Pour over bread layers. Cover with
aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at	350°
for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan promptly. Turn pan upside down.
This is a good breakfast item.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: jean's carrot cake
directions: (If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder & salt.)

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries.
Add enough Coke to make 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to boil and pour over dry jello.
Dissolve and add cream cheese and pecans and refrigerate until congealed.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, roll into balls and place on a cookie sheet, then bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a greased baking dish and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, butter and American cheese. Work spinach through like pie dough.
Mix in 6 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper.
"Dump" into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Make in a.m. and refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Boil all ingredients. Cool.
Pour over thinly sliced pickles. Refrigerate.
Will keep approximately 2 weeks, covered.

title: double-quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and flour. Beat for 2 minutes.
Add egg and butter.
Beat with mixer at medium speed until butter is smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add rest of flour and stir by hand. Scrape sides of bowl, cover with wax paper and let stand until doubles, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Stir down batter in 20 to 25 strokes and spoon into greased muffin tins, filling 1/2 full.
Let rise again for about 30 minutes or until butter reaches top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes on 425°.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, pecans and cubed pineapple.
Stir lemon juice into yogurt.
Mix gently over chicken.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix water, oil and salt in pan until boiling; turn off burner.
Add flour and mix until it comes away from sides with mixer.
Drop by heaping tablespoons onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes, lower heat to 375 degrees and bake another 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut little "cap" off the top of each puff.
Make pudding and fill each puff.
Top with "cap" and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and put oleo on top.
Set aside.
Mix next 5 ingredients and add to cooked broccoli.
Put all in greased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and cheese and bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: butternut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and an additional 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, onion and peas together.
Mix soup, milk and sour cream together and fold into chicken mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Break saltines over top and pour butter over saltines.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients plus 8 ounces of Cheddar cheese. Spread in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top the last 5 to 10 minutes.
Bake at 300° at least 1 hour.

title: shish kabob
directions: Marinate 2 pounds of tender lamb (which has been cut into 1 1/2-inch cubes) for 2 hours in mixture made up of all ingredients. Thread the marinated meat on skewers, alternating with similarly sized cuts of tomatoes, onions, green peppers and mushroom caps. Broil or cook over a grill, basting with melted butter.
Suitable cuts of veal, beef or pork can be substituted for the lamb.

title: pineapple cherry crunch
directions: Place pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling over top.
Spread dry cake mix over.
Pour melted butter over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Sprinkle with nuts before placing in oven.

title: eastern shore crab cakes(yields 6 servings)
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Shape into 6 patties.
Coat in flour.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Can be chilled in fridge all day or overnight.
Fry in butter or oleo over medium heat 4 minutes on each side or until golden.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain, shred cabbage.
Chop onion and other ingredients; cook over medium heat.
Add about 2 cups water to begin and then as needed.
Cooking time:
2 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix all together except oleo.
Place oleo on top.
Cook for 2 minutes in microwave.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon hot oil. Stir-fry half of the chicken until browned.
Remove and fry rest of chicken.
Over medium heat, add 1 tablespoon hot oil.
Stir-fry veggies.
Add ginger and garlic powder until crisp.
Add soup, soy sauce and vinegar.
Heat until boiling.
Place chicken back into skillet.
Heat and serve over rice.

title: peach cobbler (or fruit)
directions: Put butter in a pan.
Put in oven at 370° and melt it.
Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar and milk.
In another bowl, mix fruit and 1 cup of sugar.
Pour your flour mixture onto butter; don't mix up.
Pour fruit mix on top of flour mix.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Pour 1 1/2 cups tomato juice over balls.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter muffins(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients and cut in peanut butter and margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg substitute and milk; stir until moistened.
Fill 8 muffin cups that have been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange slices in greased dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder, break egg over flour mixture and mix until crumbly.
Put crumbly mix over apples and dust with cinnamon.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: ruth ann's meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, eggs, onion, pepper and celery.
Mix tomato sauce, mustard and sugar together.
Pour 1/2 the tomato sauce mixture in with rest of the items.
Mix.
Pour the other half of the tomato sauce over the meat loaf after placing loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: silverado taco casserole
directions: In lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole place 1/2 taco chips. Set aside.

title: calorie counter's coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot and onion.
Stir together yogurt, oil, horseradish, 1/8 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Toss all together.
Chill several hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable ground beef casserole
directions: Grease well a 3-quart casserole.
Slice very thin potatoes in bottom, then slice carrots, onions and celery.
On top of these, add green peas.
Drain off juice from peas and mix with tomato soup.
Save this to put on top the last thing.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat by hand, 30 seconds.
Drop by large spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 450° oven until golden brown. Mix garlic with melted margarine.
(A little paprika added to this will make them pretty.) Immediately brush biscuits with garlic butter after removing from oven.
Serve immediately.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Thaw the potatoes.
Mix all ingredients in a big bowl together and spread in shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes or until hot. Bake at 350°.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Beat until smooth.
Dip each onion ring in batter, letting excess drip in bowl.
Deep fat fry until brown.

title: layered lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour with pecans.
Melt oleo and mix with flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until browned.
Cool.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Using an electric mixer, combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat until well mixed. On a lightly floured surface, roll the dough and cut into desired shapes. Place cookies on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until just firm. Do not overbake. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sudjuki (turkish camel sausage)
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and blend very well to mix spices throughout meat.
Form into patties and fry.
A very different flavor, but very, very good.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk on low heat.
Remove. Stir in pecans. Place by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate.
Melt paraffin.
Mix. Dip caramels into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.

title: squaw bread
directions: Add enough milk or water to make a stiff dough and drop into hot grease (400°) by the tablespoonful.
Turn once and serve hot.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone chicken.
Boil chicken, broth (from boiled chicken) and soups together in pot.
Boil eggs and cut up. Cut tortillas in half and add tortillas and egg to pot.
Cook until tortillas are done.

title: faster and flameless
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to a boil.
Remove and stir in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoon size on wax paper.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix well with mixer. Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add carrots by mixing with a spoon.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350 for 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: black forest kolaches
directions: Combine
yeast,
cup
warm milk and 1/3 cup sugar. Stir until
yeast
dissolves.
Add butter, 1/2 cup warm milk, sour cream,
eggs,
salt, cocoa and 2 cups flour.
Stir well. Add rest of
flour
to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise for
30 minutes.
Mix
and
let
rise for another 30 minutes. Punch
down and
roll
out
on floured surface about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with round cookie cutter and place in 2 greased 9 x
11 x 2-inch baking pans.
Spread with melted butter.
Cover and
let
rest for 10 minutes.
Make indention with thumb and fill
with cream cheese filling and top with 1 teaspoon cherry pie
filling.
Cover and let rise until double in size (about 20 to
minutes). Bake
at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, then cool, drizzle with cocoa icing.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into ice cream freezer. Finish filling freezer with regular milk.
Freeze.

title: pecan divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to 270° to 290° on candy thermometer, soft crack stage, stirring frequently.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in mixer bowl until stiff peaks form.
Add hot syrup 1/3 at a time to egg whites, beating constantly until stiff.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Yield:
36 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Melt butter and add pecans and coconut.
Stir until toasted. Set aside to cool.
With mixer, mix cream cheese and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and beat until smooth.
Layer the following in each pie crust:
1/2 cream cheese, 1/2 coconut and pecans and 1/2 caramel.
Repeat, ending with caramel.
Pies freeze well for later use.

title: peanut butter and jam muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Beat eggs and peanut butter until smooth.
Blend in apple juice concentrate, milk and margarine.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add peanuts.
Spoon half of batter evenly into 12 greased muffin pans.
Drop 1 1/2 teaspoons strawberry fruit spread into center of each.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Combine ingredients.
Bake for 12 minutes. Cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt. Add egg yolks and a little of the milk. Stir until smooth then add the remainder of the milk and mix well. Add margarine and cook on medium high heat until it thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat and add vanilla and coconut. Pour in baked pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 5 Tbsp sugar and beat until a stiff peak forms. Spread on top and seal the sides. Sprinkle coconut on top and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread("sugar-free")
directions: Orange-flavored bread with a center of spice and nuts.

title: nana's italian ricotta pie
directions: Place Ricotta in mixer; mix.
Add sugar and flour.
Add one egg at a time alternating with cream.
Add vanilla.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs. Make sure bottom and sides are well covered.
Pour mixture into dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then reduce temperature to 300° for about 1 hour or until done (knife comes out dry).
Once cooled, store in refrigerator.

title: swiss cream steak
directions: Cover steaks with flour.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add steaks and salt and pepper.
Brown meat on both sides.
Remove meat; saute onion.
Return meat to skillet.
Cover with onion and water; mix in sour cream.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour on low heat.
Check meat and stir occasionally.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger until lightly brown; drain.
Line a casserole dish, alternating layers of hamburger, sliced raw potatoes and onion; add soup.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
Add egg, pineapple, margarine and vanilla; mix with wooden spoon until blended.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
If made as muffins, bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: joretta tysor's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and butter.
Blend in sugar and eggs (one egg at a time).
Add vanilla and flour.
Blend until smooth.
Do not overbeat.

title: caramel oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Break up 1 roll of cookie dough into large bowl.
Add 3/4 cup of the oats, 1/3 cup of the brown sugar and 1 tsp. of the vanilla; mix well.
With floured fingers, press dough mixture evenly in bottom of ungreased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 13-18 minutes or until light golden brown.
Meanwhile, break up remaining roll of cookie dough into small bowl.
Add remaining cup of oats, 1/3 cup brown sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla; mix well.
In large heavy saucepan, combine caramels, butter and sweetened condensed milk.
Cook over medium-low heat until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth, stirring frequently.
Remove partially baked crust from oven. Spread caramel mixture evenly over crust.
Crumble remaining dough mixture evenly over caramel.
Return to oven; bake an additional 18-22 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 15 minutes.
Run knife around sides of pan to loosen.
Cool about 2 hours or until completely cooled.
Using small spoon, drizzle caramel topping over bars.
Cut into bars.

title: marinade for country ribs or chicken
directions: Stir well; pour into dish with cover. Place ribs or chicken in marinade and keep refrigerated up to 3 days, covered. Shake or turn meat 3 or 4 times a day. DO NOT REUSE MARINADE. Grill over charcoal for best results.

title: fettuccine alfredo, the lighter side
directions: In a small heavy saucepan, saute garlic in the butter.
Mix together half and half, milk, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Add milk mixture to the saucepan and cook over medium heat until it begins to boil.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer until mixture thickens.

title: peanut butter thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, brown sugar and peanut butter until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder and baking soda. Gradually add to peanut butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in peanuts.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil sugar, spice (tied in bag) and cold water for 10 minutes. Put in tea leaves (tied in bag), boiling water and orange juice. Remove from heat; let steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea leaves and spices.
Reheat when needed.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken, soup, water, 1/2 stick of butter, salt and pepper on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Twenty minutes before serving, add stuffing, sage and rest of butter. Cook 20 minutes. Serve.

title: potato sourdough bread
directions: Refrigerate after 24 hours.
Feed every 3 to 5 days the same ingredients as listed except yeast.
Refrigerate after 12 hours.

title: shirley's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients (except for flour and meal).
Stir in flour and meal.
Hurry and place in pan before meal rises.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: anita's dip
directions: Mix together.
Best at room temperature.
Serve with crackers (Club, etc.).

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, evaporated milk and poppy seed.
Mix well.
Pour into bread pans. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch, syrup and water to a boil. Add jello, orange peel and Cointreau.
Allow to cool. Fill crust with sliced peaches. Pour cooled syrup over peaches.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a canister.
Spoon into cup and add hot water.
Yummy!

title: molasses cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine raisins, molasses and hot water.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature.
In a separate bowl, sift remaining ingredients together.
Stir into cooled molasses mixture until smooth.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick spray or use nonstick pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: summer squash medley
directions: Wash and slice squash, dice onion, and quarter tomato.
In heavy skillet spray well with cooking spray.
Add all ingredients. Cook on medium heat covered until vegetables are tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use ungreased cookie sheets.

title: cherries and cream
directions: Beat sour cream and sugar in small bowl.
Set aside.
Reserve 4 cherries from pie filling; set aside.
Combine remaining cherry pie filling with lemon juice.
Alternate layers of pie filling with cream mixture in 4 parfait glasses, ending with pie filling. Dollop with cream mixture, garnish with a cherry.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix together just enough to be creamy, flour and soda sifted together.
Mix the sugar, cocoa, salad dressing and water. Combine both mixtures and beat until light and fluffy.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham muffinwiches
directions: In a bowl, combine corn bread mix, mustard, milk, oil and egg just until blended. Stir in the ham and onions. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups half full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Immediately sprinkle with cheese. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan. Serve warm. Yield: 9 muffins.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and flour together.
(Take out 2 tablespoons flour to mix with fruit and nuts.)
Mix fruit and nuts with flour and coat well.
Mix all together.
Chill 1 hour.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 250°.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Mix well and pack tightly in a foil lined pan.
Decorate top of cake with cherries and pecan halves.

title: veal scallopini with tomato cream sauce
directions: Dredge veal in seasoned flour; shake off excess.
Melt butter in large skillet over high heat.
Add veal and cook about 2 minutes on each side.
Divide veal between 2 plates and tent with foil to keep warm.
Wipe out skillet.
Add cream and horseradish and boil until liquid is reduced by half.
Taste, adding more horseradish if desired.
Add tomato, parsley and chives.
Stir until heated through.
Spoon cream over veal and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix 1/4 cup in a coffee cup of hot water.
(If you use name brands it gives it a bitter taste.)

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots in a skillet and add 1 in. of water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until crisp/tender. Drain. Melt butter in
a heavy skillet and add lemon juice and brown sugar. Stir until thickened. Add carrots and stir until well glazed and heated through.

title: no-bakes
directions: Mix oatmeal, cocoa, coconut and pecans in large bowl.
Mix sugar, milk and butter in saucepan; heat over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Mix with dry ingredients and drop on wax paper. Let set until cookies are dry.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, green onions, green pepper and peas. Spread mayonnaise on top and sprinkle sugar on top of mayonnaise. Layer Cheddar cheese and crumble bacon on top.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix together and put in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole and put rice on bottom, then chicken.
Mix soups and pour over chicken and rice.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: low-fat fettucine alfredo
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles.
Bring to a boil. Simmer on low while constantly stirring.
Pour over cooked fettucine noodles.

title: bucket of dirt
directions: You will need gummy worms.

title: batter rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water in large bowl.
Stir to dissolve. Add sugar, oil, egg, salt and 3 cups of flour.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
With spoon, beat in enough remaining flour, a little at a time, until soft dough is easy to handle.
Turn out on floured board; knead until not sticky.
Place in greased bowl; cover with foil and let rise for at least 2 hours before using. Roll out again on floured board and make into rolls.
Place into greased pans and bake for 20 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: brown beef in beer
directions: Cut roast in 1 1/2 x 2-inch strips and brown in butter.
Add beef; sprinkle basil and pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until beef is tender.
Stir in gravy mix, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: icebox pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in two greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Let cool in pans for 20 minutes.

title: pronto pups
directions: You will need wooden skewers.
Blend egg and milk; stir in dry ingredients.
Insert wooden skewers in hot dogs. Dip into batter until well coated and then fry in deep hot fat (375°) until golden brown.
Serve with prepared mustard.

title: french amaretto flan
directions: You will need 12 small glass custard cups and two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.

title: smashed pear salad
directions: Drain pear juice and add water to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil in saucepan; remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Dissolve.

title: baked alaska
directions: Beat the ingredients until glossy, but not dry.
Place ice cream on top of prebaked cake; ice cream must cover top of cake. Coat completely with ice cream and bake at 500° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Ice cream will not melt!!!

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add by teaspoon to cup of hot water to taste.

title: youngstown club cheese
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Blend together all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves in boiling water. Cool.
Mix all ingredients except soup and water.
Fill leaves.
Roll and secure with toothpicks, if necessary.
Place in roasting pan.
Mix soup and water; pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: make in the blender potato pancakes
directions: Break eggs into blender container; add onion slice, salt, parsley and half of the potatoes.
Blend on high for 30 seconds. Add rest of potatoes and flour; blend until the last potato cube has been blended in.
Pour onto hot, greased griddle by tablespoonfuls.
Cook on both sides until brown.
Makes 8 pancakes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix the corn flakes and coconut together in a large bowl.
Put corn syrup in pan and heat until boiling.
Remove quickly and add peanut butter.
Stir.
Add to corn flakes and stir quickly. Spoon out on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and molasses.
Add flour, mixed with other dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Blend together sour cream and cream cheese; stir in chilies, olives, Cheddar cheese, onion and seasonings.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas and roll up.
Recommend refrigeration before cutting; makes easier.
Slice rolled up tortillas into bite size appetizers.
Serve with salsa.
May be prepared the night before; refrigerate.

title: fruit slush
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Stir in soda and freeze.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn, eggs, sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix well.
Add milk.
Blend until ingredients are covered. Cut butter into small pieces and mix into corn.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato pie
directions: Brown pie shell.
Line shell with sliced tomatoes. Mix cheese, bacon and onion.
Spread atop tomatoes.
Blend eggs, milk and mayonnaise.
Spoon on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot meat turnovers
directions: Saute onions in oil until brown.
Add ground meat.
Season with salt, pepper, parsley flakes and dill weed to taste.
Cook until done.
Add eggs.
Let mixture cool.
Fill dough triangles and cook until brown in a 325° oven.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple chunks in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and grated cheese.
Pour over pineapple chunks.
Top with margarine and Ritz cracker crumbs, mixed together.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. When done, take pineapple and sugar; heat on top of stove until sugar is dissolved.
Do not let boil.
Poke holes in cake, pour pineapple mixture over top of cake.
Cook vanilla pie filling as directed.
Pour evenly over pineapple.
Let cool; top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: diet dip(low calorie, low-fat)
directions: Blend together.
Use as a dip for vegetables, or can use as a salad dressing.
Recipe can be doubled.
2 Tbsp. = 50 calories.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour and shortening (like you would for pie crust).
Mix eggs, sugar and flavoring together. Mix soda, baking powder, cream of tartar and milk together.
Pour this into the egg mixture.
Pour this mixture into the flour and shortening mix.
Knead lightly on a floured board.
Roll thin; cut out.
Bake in a hot oven until brown.

title: cranberry almond pound cake
directions: 2 hours before baking:
Heat amaretto in small saucepan.
Add dried cranberries.
Let cool, stirring occasionally until fruit has soaked up all the liquid.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle crumbled bacon in chilled pie crust.
In a bowl, beat eggs, cream, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425 degres for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325 degrees; continue to bake for 30-40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll into ball.
Sprinkle pepper all around the top.
Good with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine soup, water chestnuts and oleo in saucepan and simmer 10 minutes on low heat.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix everything but chocolate chips together until most of the lumps are gone.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour batter into Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Do not test.
It will look craggy and lumpy on top.
Not to worry. Let it cool in pan for 30 minutes.
Take it out then and pour hot glaze over top.

title: fresh seafood casserole
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter until very soft. Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Arrange tomatoes in 8 x 8 x 2-inch square glass dish.
Shake oil, vinegar, oregano, salt, pepper, mustard and garlic in a tightly covered jar.
Pour over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate, spooning dressing over tomatoes occasionally, at least 2 hours. Arrange on lettuce leaves.
Sprinkle with onion and parsley. Drizzle with dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gorton
directions: In pot, combine meat and onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover meat with water; heat to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly for three hours; turn heat off.
Remove excess fat from pot with ladle.
Leave enough liquid so meat will not be dry. Add cloves, cinnamon, ginger and allspice; mix well.
Makes great pork pies or turkey stuffing.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, mandarin oranges, oil and eggs.
Pour into three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: drunken hot dogs
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cut hot dogs into small pieces.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop into hot vegetable oil by large spoonfuls until golden.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
In saucepan, bring to boil oleo, Crisco, water, cocoa and vanilla.
Add boiled mixture to flour and sugar.
Mix.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Mix and pour in a greased and floured jelly roll pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost immediately.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Prepare jello and mix with strawberries.
Crumble up cake and pour jello and strawberry mixture over it.
Be sure all juice is soaked up.
Chill.
Spread Cool Whip over top or add as served.

title: egg nog cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and shortening.
Add sugar, then add egg and vanilla.
Mix in nutmeg, flour, baking powder and salt. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly.
Do not overcook.
Saute onion in margarine.
Cook rice in 2 cups water.
Drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients, saving small amount of cheese for top of casserole.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead.
Also freezes well.
Allow extra 15 minutes cooking time if casserole has been refrigerated.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes until done.

title: coconut sponge surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10 x 6-inch Pyrex pan or a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually. Cream until light and fluffy.
Add yolks and beat well.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt.
Blend in.
Fold in coconut, flour and milk. Beat egg whites until very stiff and carefully fold into yolk batter until no egg white shows.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Set in a pan of hot water in a 375° oven.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve warm at room temperature or chill, if desired.
Garnish with whipped cream and toasted coconut.

title: blueberry muffins(the best)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.

Beat in vanilla and sour cream. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Stir into butter mixture. Fold in blueberries. Spoon into muffin tins and sprinkle with sugar. Bake 23 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut bread into 4 to 5 strips.
Bake bread strips on cookie sheet for 2 hours at 200°.
Mix peanut butter, honey and cooking oil.
Dip baked bread strips in the mixture and roll in crushed vanilla wafers.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in
large mixing bowl.
Beat until thoroughly	mixed.	Pour
into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze. Can be served frozen (tastes like ice cream) or thawed.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown 1 pound of hamburger meat along with green bell pepper and onion.
Mix French's chili mix, chili powder, tomatoes, 3 cups water, hamburger, and pinto beans in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Let set for about 10 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Pour off liquid from yams.
With electric mixer, mix until like mashed potatoes.
Take beaters out and rinse to get rid of the strings from potatoes.
Add eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla, margarine and pineapple and mix well.
Stir in pecans and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and return to oven to brown marshmallows.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and divide into 3 parts.
Shape into rolls and roll in chili powder.
Refrigerate until serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Put Crispix cereal on cookie sheet and pour over mixture.
Mix with powdered sugar in large grocery bag.
Store in an airtight container.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, and beer.
Put into greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour butter on top. Put back in oven for 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Prepare berries.
Add lemon juice and cook 3 minutes. Add sugar.
Stir until dissolved and cook 6 minutes.
Let cool, stirring occasionally. Seal in sterile jar.
(Put in crock bowl overnight before sealing.)

title: rocket salad
directions: For each serving, place a crisp lettuce leaf on a salad plate. Launching pad: 1 slice pineapple.
Rocket: 1/2 peeled banana (set upright in center of pineapple slice).
Nose Cone: 1/2 cherry fastened to top of banana with a toothpick.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Bake at 325° until done.
Makes cake or muffins.

title: homemade diaper wipes
directions: Cut the roll of paper towels in half and remove the cardboard center.
Mix the liquids in an old baby wipe container (Wash-A-Bye baby brand).
Place half a roll of paper towels in the container, put the lid on and turn upside down to let towels soak.
When ready to use pull the towels from the center of roll.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Place spices in bag and tie securely.
Put bag of spices into pot of sugar and water.
Bring only to a boil.
This syrup can be made ahead of time and keeps well in the refrigerator.
Add pineapple and cranberry juice to mixture; mix well.
Heat.
Add rum flavoring to taste and red food coloring to brighten.
Add dots of butter and serve in mugs with cinnamon sticks as stirrers, if desired.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, melted margarine, flour, cocoa and vanilla together.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts in unbaked pie crust shell and pour filling over nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip sprinkled with remaining nuts and grated chocolate.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Dissolve butter in boiling water.
Add flour and cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Cool until warm.
Beat in 1 whole egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Shape into 12 to 15 eclairs on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 15 minutes and then at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix together well and make 3 "wells" (or holes).
In the first well, put the vinegar.
In the second well, put the vanilla. In the third well, put the oil.
Mix together.
Add 2 cups cold water. Stir. Don't mix.
Pour into an oblong ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir beef until brown; drain. Stir in chilies, seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently, until thickened, 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread beans over baked crust.
Top with beef mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and onion. Serve with sauce.

title: plenty o'peanuts snack bar
directions: Grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine cereal and peanuts in large bowl.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, to a full rolling boil.
Remove mixture from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over cereal mixture, mixing until well coated. Press mixture into prepared pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Place small scoop of ice cream on one cookie and top with another cookie.
Continue until you are finished.
Work in small batches and quickly.
Place the filled cookies on a cookie sheet lined with waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Cover and freeze until set.
(If making large amounts, turn the freezer setting up.)
May be individually wrapped after set.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: To prepare watermelon rind, trim dark skin and pink flesh from thick watermelon rind; wash and cut in one-inch pieces.
Dissolve lime in 2 quarts of water; pour over rind.
If needed, add more water to cover rind.
Let stand 2 hours in lime.
Drain; rinse and cover rind with cold water.
Cook until just tender; drain.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Combine spices with remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Add watermelon rind and simmer until clear.
Add boiling water if syrup becomes too thick before rind is clear.
Remove spice bag.
Pack, boiling hot, into jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space.
Adjust lids.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Add salt and let stand 2 hours or overnight if more convenient.
Drain well.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Place into containers and freeze.

title: feather bed rolls
directions: Scald the milk; remove from stove and add shortening and sugar.
When cool, add yeast which has been dissolved in a little water.
Then add flour and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Beat again.

title: pizza dip
directions: Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Mix softened cream cheese, finely chopped onions and dissolved bouillon together.
Add pizza sauce to taste.
Best if it is refrigerated for several hours. Serve with potato chips.

title: squash bird feeder
directions: Cut off part of squash and scoop out insides.
Put 2 holes in top with nail and hammer.
Use the nail to push string through each hole.
Tie the ends together.
Fill with bird seed and hang in tree.

title: steak soup
directions: Melt the margarine and whip in flour to make

a smooth paste. Stir in cold water. Saut the ground beef; drain off grease and add to soup. Add the onions, carrots and celery which have been pan boiled. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer and cook until vegetables are done. DO NOT SALT. May be frozen.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine Bisquick and milk with 15 strokes. Grease 12 muffin cups.
Roll dough on lightly dusted/Bisquick board.
Knead 8 to 10 times to smooth dough.
Roll into 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll tightly widthwise and seal well.
Cut into 12 (1-inch) slices.
Set in muffin cups.
Bake 15 minutes, until brown.

title: spinach pie
directions: Clean and chop spinach and put in large mixing bowl.
Add cheeses and seasonings.
Add egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into spinach mixture.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan and put 6 pastry sheets in pan, brushing each with melted butter.
Spread spinach mixture evenly and cover with 6 more pastry sheets and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cut in squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheese meatballs
directions: Mix the cracker crumbs and eggs together first.
Combine the ground beef, cheese, salt, pepper, crumb mixture and chili pepper or chili powder.
Mixture will be stiff.
Form into balls (size of golf balls).
Roll in flour.
Place in 2-quart casserole and cover with the sauce.
Mix and bring to a boil the remaining ingredients. Pour over the meatballs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour and uncovered for 1/2 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and pour over cabbage just to moisten.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine ingredients and form into a ball.
Do not knead. Divide into 2 parts.
Roll each part on lightly floured surface until thin.
Dry 10 minutes.
Cut into strips of desired width and length.
Have seasoned broth ready and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Pieces of chicken or other meat may be added if you like.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy party treats
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin pan with Pam no-stick spray.
Blend baking mix and milk to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead approximately 20 times.
Roll dough into a rectangle, about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out circles with 4-inch cookie cutter.
Press circles into prepared muffin pans.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 1/2 cup freezer containers.
Freeze fruit 8 hours.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Mix Jell-O with one cup of boiling water.
Add the cranberry fruit and stir.
Stir in the pineapple, then walnuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mom watkins' turkey gravy
directions: Make
thickening
with flour and water.
Stir in turkey stock, slowly,
to
keep from being lumpy.
Cook until thick. Add a little milk and finish cooking.
Add turkey meat, cut in small pieces.
Salt and pepper.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until cooked and tear into bite size pieces. Grease a large casserole dish. Crush chips and spread 1/2 of the chips into bottom of dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour 1/2 of the mixture in dish.
Layer the rest of the crushed chips and top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling in Dutch oven, stirring occasionally; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender, about 25 minutes.

title: good ole potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Stir in chopped eggs, onions and relish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in desired amount of mayonnaise and mustard; mix well.
Serves 6 to 8.
Garnish with sliced eggs; sprinkle with paprika.

title: colorful fruit punch
directions: Dilute lemonade and pour into punch bowl with ginger ale.
Add frozen juice cubes.

title: chicken casserole("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Put in 2-quart casserole.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Add cereal. Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Use as desired.
Do not stir before using.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook "California Blend" until tender; drain.
Add soup (undiluted) and Velveeta cheese; mix.
Mix melted butter and crackers.
Put on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: ann's beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Dough will be loose.
Do not add more flour, and do not knead.
Does not need to rise.
Grease 1 loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Butter top, then brown 15 minutes.

title: low-cal oven fried fish
directions: Combine milk, salt, Worcesteshire sauce and onion in medium bowl.
Mix together the cornflakes, parsley, mustard and paprika on wax paper.
Dip the fish in the milk mixture and then in the crumb mixture.
Grease a shallow baking dish with 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Arrange fish fillets in dish.
Drizzle the remaining butter over the fish.
Bake in 500° oven until fish flakes, 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings, 145 calories per serving

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Beat flour, butter, sugar and salt until mixture resembles crumbs.
Heavily grease bottom and sides of a 15 x 10-inch baking pan, at least 1 1/2-inches deep.
Press mixture firmly into pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shirley's peach cobbler
directions: Drain most of juice off peaches. Place in a large saucepan with 3/4 cup sugar. Bring to a boil. Beat together flour, baking powder, salt, 1 cup sugar, milk and egg. Pour boiling fruit into an 8 or 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Don't put more than 1/2-inch of juice in baking dish. Pour the batter over the hot peaches. Melt 1/2 cup butter. Pour butter over the batter into drizzle. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: feather sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add water; continue beating until very thick.
Gradually beat in sugar; add vanilla and extract.
Fold in flour that has been sifted with salt, adding a little at a time.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until forms glossy peaks.
Fold into batter. Pour into ungreased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Frost with Butter Frosting.

title: butterfinger cake(fly-ash cake)
directions: Mix cake as directed on box; bake.
While still hot, poke holes in cake with straw.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping in the holes in the cake.
When cool, spread on Cool Whip and Butterfingers.
(I put the Butterfingers in my Salad Shooter to grind them up.)

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make the day ahead and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Will freeze.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450. Bake pie crust 5-7 minutes or until golden. Remove from oven & let cool. Reset oven to 325°.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop fine.
Set caps aside. Preheat oven to 450°.
In skillet cook sausage until well browned. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Coat stems in drippings and cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sausage, cheese and bread crumbs.
Fill caps with mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve hot.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place meat in a casserole.
Mix mushroom soup, onion soup mix and Burgundy wine.	Pour over meat and bake, covered, in 325° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Do not peak.
It comes out brown.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Keeps well in refrigerator and also freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: golden rich bars
directions: In a bowl, mix cake batter, butter and 2 eggs.
Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread evenly.
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs until fluffy.
Pour mixture over first layer.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
The cake will look somewhat like a custard.
Do not bake until firm. Cake should be soft in the middle.

title: low cholesterol chicken supreme
directions: Pound each piece of chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spray a large skillet with Pam cooking spray.
Preheat skillet.
Cook until tender and not pink.
Transfer to
platter.

title: pecan shortbread
directions: Using electric mixer, in large bowl, beat butter at medium speed until creamy. At low speed, beat in sugar, then flour. Do not overbeat. Stir in pecans by hand. Press dough evenly in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 300 degrees for 40 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool and cut into 1 1/2 inch squares.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Drain. Combine other ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over tortilla chips.

title: favorite chewy bars
directions: Combine sugar and white corn syrup and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Add Rice Krispies to mixture and press into buttered jelly roll pan. Bake in a jelly roll pan.
Makes 32 to 40 bars.

title: marshmallow balls
directions: In a pan combine toffee bars, milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat about 20 minutes until toffee is melted, stirring often.
Cool slightly.
Dip marshmallows in toffee mixture.
Roll in cereal.
Dry on wax paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a bowl.
Warm the milk and
add
to
bowl.
Mix
thoroughly.	Add cheese and butter. Mix.
Add	remaining flour, mix well and set aside in a
warm place, covered for 1 hour.	Punch down dough and wait 15
minutes. Punch down again and form into a round ball in a pan
and	allow to rise for 1 hour.
Place in a 12-inch Dutch oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Heat soup, onion and cheese until cheese melts.
Add hominy. Pour into casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
If you microwave it, topping can be browned in oven for a few minutes.
You can use crushed crackers for topping instead of corn flakes.
Serves 10-12.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients and put into greased 9 x 12 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: onion bread
directions: This recipe as listed and used will do about 4 slices of bread.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled, etc., to serve different size groups.

title: curried black beans and rice with sausage
directions: Heat oil in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Cook onion and curry powder, stirring well, until onion is tender.
Stir in sausage and broth; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Cook until hot, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vinegar. Spoon over rice.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Bring eggs, sugar, flour and vinegar to a boil. Remove from heat and add apples, pineapple, peanuts and Cool Whip. Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving. Serves 10 to 12.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; cool and turn into a large bowl.
Fold in mayonnaise, cheese, chiles, pimiento and scallions.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old fashion lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add lemon juice, grated rind and egg yolks.
Pour hot water over ingredients.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; add oleo.
Pour filling in baked pie crust.
Top with beaten egg whites.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Mix well and pour into casserole dish.

title: carrot salad
directions: Scrape carrots and grate in food processor.
Add raisins and pineapple.
Mix with yogurt.

title: spice mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sugar in a large bowl.
Sift flour and all other dry ingredients together.
Combine the 3/4 cup water and the corn syrup in a small bowl.
Add dry ingredients to the mayonnaise mixture alternately with the water-corn syrup mixture, blending well after each addition until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Good iced with a caramel icing.

title: 9 layer salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in the bottom of a large mixing bowl. Layer on peppers, onion, celery and green peas in that order.

title: german green beans
directions: Cut bacon into small cubes.
In small saucepan, add bacon and chopped onion.
Cook and stir until bacon is semi-crisp.
Add flour; stir until well mixed (bubbly).
Add vinegar, sugar and juice from can of beans.
Mix well and allow to boil for about a minute.
Add beans and season with salt and pepper.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots, onion and celery in margarine.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook 1 minute.
Slowly add milk and chicken broth, cook until thick.
Stir in baking soda and cheese until melted. Add broccoli and simmer for one hour.

title: mom's banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, salt and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add mashed bananas and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, then vanilla and nuts and mix well.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a sheet cake pan.
Line bottom with pecans and then coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt butter and cream cheese.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Spoon on top of German chocolate cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and form with tablespoon on lightly sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Then chill until thick.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello and marshmallows in 1 1/2 cups water.
Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice and chill for a few minutes.
When this begins to set, add crushed pineapple with cream cheese, nuts and mayonnaise. Fold in Cool Whip when the mixture is thick enough to hold. Chill and serve.

title: jellied waldrop salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water; chill until thickened.
Pour lemon juice over diced apple.
Add apple, celery, raisins and nuts to gelatin.
Pour in mold.
Chill until firm.

title: filhos (portuguese donuts)
directions: Dissolve butter in lukewarm milk.
Dissolve yeast cakes.
Beat eggs until very light.
Add to butter, yeast and milk mixture. Mix remaining ingredients into liquid mixture, mixing well.
Let rise until double in size.
Stretch small amount of dough into shape, leaving a hole in the middle.
Fry in oil until browned on both sides.
Makes 80 good size donuts.

title: goop
directions: Mix ingredients.
Makes gooey, squishy stuff to play with, much like Gak and similar products.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
This tastes better left overnight in refrigerator.

title: green potato pies
directions: Bake potatoes and cut them in half lengthwise.
Scoop the potatoes from the skins into a mixing bowl.
Add milk and margarine and mash the potatoes.
Stir in cheese and spinach. Then scoop the mixture back into the potato skins.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best ever dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple in bottom of baking dish.
Pour cherries over. Top with dry cake mix.
Pour melted butter over.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: In covered 10-inch skillet with 1 inch boiling water, cook cauliflower until tender-crisp.
Drain.
In same skillet, place butter and heat.
Add pepper and mushrooms and cook until tender. Stir in soup and liquid.
Mix well.
Add cheese and pimento. Return cauliflower to skillet and heat through.
Place in serving dish and sprinkle parsley on top.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; mix in sugar, vanilla and vegetable oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in cut up apples and nuts (dough will be very thick).
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: corn and clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Combine other ingredients with onion and bring to a simmer.
Simmer for 5 minutes and serve.

title: caramel nut crunch
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Line with graham crackers. Combine and boil butter and sugar until well blended (about 1 minutes).
Add nuts and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Core peppers; cut in halves and remove seed.
Cook in boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain.
Brown beef and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine rice and beef.
Add bran, wheat germ, soup and oregano.
Place peppers in large baking dish.
Place some of the meat mixture in each pepper half.
Top each with a dab of catsup.
Put 1/2-inch water in bottom of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Combine.
Let chicken set overnight in marinade.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then at 375° until brown; baste every 15 minutes.

title: spinach-cheese potato skins
directions: Pierce potatoes in several places with fork.
Wrap potatoes in paper towels.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, turning paper over once.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: sausage zucchini bake
directions: Place sausage in frying pan and add 1 cup of water.
Let water boil off and fry at low heat until brown.
Slice onion and peppers into thin rings.
In a large casserole dish, combine sausage, onion, pepper, crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, zucchini and garlic.
Grate Mozzarella cheese and add to top.
Add Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with shell macaroni on the side.

title: twinkie cakes
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Let cool. Remove from pan.
Let it cool completely.
Split into two layers with a thread.
While cake is cooling, combine the 5 tablespoons flour and
milk.
Boil until thick. Stir constantly. Let cool. Combine sugar, milk, salt, shortening and butter with mixer for 15 minutes. Add flour and beat 3 more minutes. Spread on one layer.
Add top. Cut into pieces.

title: apricot crunch
directions: In a large bowl combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Cut in butter until particles are small and uniform.
Pat half of mix in 9-inch ungreased square pan.
Spread filling on top of that. Sprinkle remaining mix over top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Stir sugar, butter and water together over low heat until dissolved.
Add pecans and stir constantly until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and drop onto marble or wax paper, making small patties, about 2-inches in diameter.
