title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar into a large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening (at room temperature), molasses and vanilla.
With a wooden spoon, stir until smooth about 1 1/2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and oatmeal; stir until it is blended evenly.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls and 4 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: ham rolls continental
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Top ham slices with cheese.
Place broccoli spears on each slice and roll. Secure with toothpicks. Place in shallow baking dish.
Cook onion rings in margarine until tender.
Gradually add milk, stir until thickened.
Pour over ham, cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: corn pones
directions: Grease the skillet well with drippings or pork rind.
Mix corn meal and salt in bowl.
Pour in cup of boiling water and stir. Add more boiling water, 1/4 cup at a time, until you have a stiff dough that can be shaped with the hands.
Bake in prepared skillet at 400° until golden.
Serves 6.

title: champagne punch
directions: Pour over ice that was frozen in a Bundt pan.
Looks like a Christmas wreath.
Float flowers in it and let it freeze.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and taco seasoning mix together. Drain fat.
Mix Cream soups together.
In a crock pot layer 1/2 hamburger mixture, 1/2 soup mixture, and 1/2 crushed chips.
Make a second layer in the same order using the rest of the ingredients.
Top with taco sauce and Cheddar Cheese soup.
Cook on low 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: old-fashion chocolate cake icing
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Cook, stirring well, for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat, sit pan in pan of ice water.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Will ice 2 layers or 1 (9 x 13 x 2-inch) cake.

title: sesame seed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Soak overnight in mixture of milk, eggs and garlic powder.
Batter chicken in pancake mixture and sesame seed.
Fry in deep fat until browned.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Use a 1-quart casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend all ingredients together.
Empty all ingredients into casserole dish and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers or chips.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Drain cherries and spread into 2 baked pie crusts.
Keep out 2 cherries to go on top of each pie.
Combine milk, sugar, flour and egg yolks in large pot. Cook until custard becomes very thick. Pour over cherries in each crust.
Use egg whites and 6 tablespoons of sugar to make meringue.
Place 1 cherry on top of each pie and brown.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over cereal and let stand until cereal has absorbed water and cooled.
Cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs one at a time. Add flour, salt and buttermilk; mix until smooth.
Blend cereal mixture into batter. Add raisins and All-Bran cereal.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese soften; whip until fluffy.
Gradually add condensed milk while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into prepared crust. Chill an hour or two before covering top of pie filling with Blueberry Sauce.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, leaving just a little juice.
Stir in sugar, flour and cheese.
Pour into large casserole dish (13 x 9-inch). Cover with crushed Tid-Bits crackers.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 35 to 40 minutes at 350°, or lightly browned.

title: french cherry dessert
directions: Prepare Dream Whip.
Mix cheese and sugar together and add to Dream Whip.
Pour over baked crust.
Top with 2 cans of cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: theresa mihalyi's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper and freeze until firm.
Melt together chocolate chips, shortening and paraffin.
Dip frozen balls into melted chips.
Let stand until chocolate is set.
(I put them back in the freezer; they set faster.)
Store in a container in layers between waxed paper. They will keep longer in the freezer than at room temperature.

title: pickled deli beets
directions: Combine all ingredients with 2 cups of cooked beets.
Cover and simmer 7 minutes.
Chill for 2 hours and serve.

title: self-rising flour biscuits
directions: Mix lightly and pat out.
Bake at 450°.

title: turkey-cheese meltaway casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, drain.
Melt 1/4 cup butter, add onion and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, thyme and pepper.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Arrange 1/2 of macaroni in bottom of lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Put 1/2 of the turkey over macaroni.
Arrange cheese slices over turkey.
Repeat layering once.
Pour sauce over all.
Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons melted butter and parsley.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip fork in flour or sugar and press fork to crisscross on cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: grandma's divinity
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Cook over medium-high heat until it threads when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add vanilla and salt to hot syrup mixture.
Beat until stiff and dull.
Add pecans and mix well. Pour onto buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Grandma said it must be a sunny day with low humidity in the kitchen for this to work.

title: quick cool "dump" salad
directions: "Dump" the Cool Whip in a bowl and sprinkle dry jello in and mix well.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple. Chill at least 15 minutes before serving.
For variety, add a can of well drained mandarin oranges and nuts (pecans or walnuts).

title: blackberry-swirl cobbler
directions: In a small saucepan, heat the water and 3/4 cup sugar to boiling, stirring to dissolve sugar for a syrup.
Set aside.
Pour the melted butter or margarine into a 10-inch pie plate or baking dish.
Set aside.

title: country-fried cabbage
directions: Heat bacon fat in 10-inch iron skillet.
Add shredded cabbage. Cook over low heat.
Stir frequently until lightly browned. Cover and cook, stirring, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Add sliced onion, if desired.
Simmer until onion is sauteed.
Serve hot with hot-water cornbread or crackling bread.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo then add well beaten eggs.
Add crushed wafers and baking powder and then milk.
Add coconut and nuts. Bake in oblong dish 9x13-inch for 30 to 35 minutes at 325.

title: cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add milk and peanut butter.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking soda, then spread out dough on wax paper.
Spread on melted chocolate chips.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill 1/2 to 1 hour in refrigerator, then slice and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: To Make Crust:
Mix powdered sugar, butter and flour together. Press into an ungreased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Cook hamburger on top of stove. Drain excess fat. Add all ingredients except corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Break corn chips in small pieces.
Place on top of casserole. Leave in oven for 5 minutes.

title: fish supreme
directions: Remove bones and skin of fish; pound.
Rub through a strainer. Cook bread crumbs and cream in a double boiler for 10 minutes. Add butter and seasoning.
When cold, add fish and beat thoroughly.
Add well-beaten eggs and place in buttered ring mold. Set mold in a deep pan with hot water to 1 inch of top.
Cover mold with wax paper.
Bake in a moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: An easy-to-make oatmeal toffee crust covered with two chocolates and nuts.

title: stir and roll biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Measure milk and oil together.
Mix with fork.
Put on wax paper.
Knead between paper. Put about 1/4 to 1/2-inches apart. Cut with cutter, placing on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 475° for 12 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Saute vegetables in bacon fat for 5 minutes.
Add bean stock and ham hocks.
Cook until beans are almost done.
Add rice and cook until rice is tender.
Add seasonings and vinegar.
Serve with chopped onion.

title: garlic cheese chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Spread each with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Roll up to enclose cheese and secure with toothpick.
Melt butter and onions and saute until soft.
Remove with slotted spoon and set aside.

title: gourmet vegetable cheese soup
directions: *I usually omit these carrots since there are carrots in frozen veggies.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Fold in cherries.
Bake in greased and floured large tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Set temperature at 275° and bake for 2 hours.

title: baked sandwiches(serves 4)
directions: Make four sandwiches, using bread, turkey and Swiss cheese. Place in buttered, square pan.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over sandwiches.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Mix in cheese and chilies.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: best in the west beans
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add bacon, onion, sugars, catsup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Put in crock-pot and add beans.
Let cook on high for 1 hour.
Turn on low and cook all night.

title: vegetable beef soup with dumplings
directions: In a large saucepan, combine tomato juice and all soups.
Stir until well blended.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer. In a medium bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder, milk and eggs.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls into simmering soup.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, or until dumplings are firm. Serve immediately.

title: sandies
directions: Cream margarine
and
sugar;
add water and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and nuts; chill 3 or 4 hours.
Shape into balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven at 325° about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar. Makes 5 dozen.

title: coconut tukras
directions: Lightly toast sesame seeds (with just a pinch of salt) on a heavy skillet.
Set aside.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In
large
Dutch
oven
cook onions, carrot, celery and garlic in
hot
oil until onion is tender but not brown.
Stir in chicken
or
beef broth, undrained tomatoes, tomato juice, cabbage and
basil.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with rye bread.

title: orange marshmallow meringue pie
directions: Cut marshmallows into quarters; set aside.
In top of double boiler, combine flour, sugar,
water, and marshmallows.
Add orange zest, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring frequently for 20 minutes or until thickened.
Remove pan from heat; add margarine.
Combine a small amount of orange mixture with egg yolks.
Combine the egg yolk mixture with the mixture in top of double boiler.
Cook 2 minutes.
Turn filling into pie shell.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, baking soda, walnuts and last, the mashed bananas.
Put in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry sundaes
directions: In a blender, combine milk, cherries, honey and almond extract; cover and process until well blended. Serve over coffee ice cream; sprinkle with grated chocolate. Yummy!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer 3 to 4 hours, then heat again before serving.
Boil water with 2 teaspoons salt.
Put in 1 pound spaghetti and cook until done.
Drain with cool water.
Pour on sauce and serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring oleo and water to a boil; sift flour and salt.
Add to water all at once and beat until thick, smooth and comes away from sides of pan.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Drop from tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes approximately 15.

title: polka daters
directions: Mix together dates and hot water.
Set aside and cool.
Beat butter sugar and eggs until creamy.
Gradually stir in flour and baking soda.
Stir in date mixture.
Add vanilla and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix warm water with yeast, salt and sugar.
Beat egg with olive oil.
Add to dough mix.
Add any seasonings.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well.
Dump last cup of flour on table; pour mix into it.
Knead a few minutes.
Let rise in large, oiled bowl, covered with cloth, at room temperature until doubled.
Makes one 12 x 24-inch cookie sheet size dough.
Can also freeze in Saran Wrap and use at a later date.
No need to let rise again; just thaw and use.

title: johnbenghetti
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger meat, onion and green pepper. Brown and drain.
Add tomato soup, mushroom soup, mushrooms and pimentos.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix with meat mixture and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry meatballs(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Combine cornstarch and water in small bowl; stir until smooth. In large skillet, combine the rest of ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook, stirring until it thickens.
Stir in meatballs,
transfer to a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight to allow flavors to blend.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat, stirring constantly. Add peanuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: antipasto pasto salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir oil, vinegar, garlic, basil, salt and oregano.
Add warm twists and cheese.
Toss to coat well.
Stir in broccoli, tomatoes, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Cover; chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: red clam sauce(low-fat)
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, saute the onions, mushrooms and garlic in the oil over medium-low heat for about 5 minutes or until onions are translucent.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, for about 45 minutes.
Makes about 8 cups. Serve over your choice of pasta.
Freezes well.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Rub into steak.
Brown meat in fat.
Place tomatoes and onion on pieces of steak.
Add water and steam until tender.

title: mystery cookie bars
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix.
Bake in greased 10 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Coat with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: pizza soup
directions: In a medium saucepot, add beef and all ingredients, except the pizza sauce, tomatoes and the water. Saut until the beef is done; add the pizza sauce, tomatoes and the water. Let simmer for 1/2 hour. Garnish with cheese.

title: marshmallow-cherry cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan, grease and flour.

title: sherry's potatoes romanoff(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Bake potatoes until fork-tender.
Peel and shred into large bowl.
Stir in sour cream, 1 cup grated cheese, salt, pepper and onion.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter or margarine and vanilla together on low speed of electric mixer until light.
Gradually add powdered sugar and beat until fluffy.
If needed, add milk until spreading consistency.

title: ancient old english cream scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Sift the flour with baking powder and salt. Cut the butter into the flour with a pastry blender or two knives until it looks like coarse meal. Stir the honey or sugar, the egg and cream together. Add the flour to the flour mixture. Beat well, but do not overwork. Pat the dough on a floured board or between sheets of wax paper until about 1/2-inch thick. Cut into rounds, squares or triangles. Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Yields 4 scones.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 2 hours.
Put in jars; seal. Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 quarts and 4 pints.

title: turnip and potato soup
directions: Slice turnips.
Simmer in enough water to cover with 1 cup chicken broth until almost tender.
Add potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add 2 or 3 cups chicken broth and 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Blend in blender.
If too thick, add a little more chicken broth.
Heat; sprinkle with paprika.

title: crispy chicken
directions: *I use jar of minced garlic instead of fresh garlic.

title: fried country style steak
directions: Place a little grease in frying pan; add a steak.
Let fry until brown on both sides, about 15 minutes.
Fill another pan with water and bring to boil.
Take steak out of frying pan and place in water.
Cook in water until you break one open and it's not red in center.
Take steak out of water and replace back in frying pan. Steak gravy recipe follows.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Crush cookies.
Mix cookies and butter.
Press into large (13 x 9-inch) Pyrex dish.
Save a little crumb mixture for topping.

title: easy linguine with red clam sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, cook garlic in hot olive oil until soft. Add cooking wine and simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Add minced clams and spaghetti sauce; heat through.
Pour over cooked linguine and top with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: microwave cooked vidalia onions
directions: Peel and cut root end off each onion so that it will sit level.
Remove about 1/2-inch core from each onion.
Press 1 tablespoon butter into cored center and sprinkle paprika over the top.
Place in 9-inch baking dish; cover with plastic wrap (leave one corner open for vent).
Cook on High power for 12 to 14 minutes or until tender.
Let stand for 5 minutes; sprinkle with salt before serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Add corn, milk and dry ingredients, beating lightly after each addition.
Add chili peppers and half of cheese.
Pour into a greased dish and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Good with any kind of cooked dried bean.

title: heath bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Line small cookie sheet with foil, then line with crackers.
Pour mixture
over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Put in freezer for 20 minutes.
Break apart.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold pineapple and cream cheese into Dream Whip and pour into pie shell.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: deep-south ovenly chicken
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving:
In large open roasting pan in 400° oven, melt butter or margarine.
Meanwhile, on waxed paper, combine baking mix, chopped pecans, paprika, salt and poultry seasoning.
Into pie plate, pour evaporated milk.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then coat well with baking mix mixture. Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in roasting pan.
Bake chicken 30 minutes.
With pancake turner, carefully turn chicken pieces.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until juices run clear when chicken is pierced with a fork, covering with foil after 10 minutes if chicken begins to brown too quickly.
Arrange chicken on platter.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix and refrigerate butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla ice cream.
Freeze.
To serve, combine 2 tablespoons of mix to 1 shot of rum and top with hot water.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper, paprika and rosemary, if desired.
Place in a 3 1/2-quart slow cooker.
Mix water/wine, soup and mushrooms until well blended.
You may add sour cream and flour mixture if you will be cooking on low temperature, 6 to 8 hours.
Pour liquid over chicken breasts.
Add paprika or cook on high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, adding sour cream/flour mixture last 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Bake in 8-inch greased pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana-applesauce cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well in large bowl of electric mixer. Add next 4 ingredients. Blend, then beat at medium speed until creamy. Add eggs and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Stir nuts and raisins and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan lined on bottom with waxed paper. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Turn out on cake rack and peel off paper. Turn right side up and while still warm, sift confectioners sugar over top. Can use loaf pans. Bake over 1 hour.

title: spanish chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in hot oil until brown.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, cinnamon, cumin and pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Drain fat.

title: pat's zucchini appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Grease oblong pan (9x13x2 in.)
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown about 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces about 1 x 2 inches.
Makes about 2 dozen appetizers.

title: fun crisp pickles
directions: Buy 1 jar whole dill pickles (cheap kind will work).
Drain the pickles.
Cut pickles in chunk slices.
Put sugar and vinegar in bowl; add pickle chunks and stir once in a while for 2 or 3 days.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 9-inch square baking pan with foil and grease foil.
Stir sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla into chocolate mixture. Pour into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with walnuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes to make cutting easier.
Peel off foil.
Cut into 12 squares.

title: harvest punch
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over tea bags.
Steep 5 minutes. Dissolve sugar in warm tea.
Add fruit juices and water.
Serve hot.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Grease 9 x 13-inch dish (use Pam if desired).
Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper; pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate. Can be completely assembled the night before.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fry bacon slightly and chop.
Add onion until golden.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until tender and most of sauce is absorbed (about 25 minutes).

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add salad oil, eggs, vanilla and lemon flavoring and mix well.
Add grated carrots and chopped nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool before frosting.

title: harvard beets
directions: Blend dry ingredients, add vinegar and mix to a smooth paste. Cook 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and sliced beets.
Simmer over low heat.
Add butter.
Serve hot.

title: neiman-marcus cafe cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix these ingredients together well, then add last 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 56 cookies.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant and onion in boiling water to cover for 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain and add crumbled bread and next 7 ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, greased.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered, or until slightly brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese stuffed celery
directions: Mix sour cream with cottage cheese; stir in radishes and chives.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika; mix well.
Fill celery with cheese mixture.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In large bowl, mix peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Then add egg and vanilla; add flour, salt and soda. Shape into balls and dip in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and press Hershey Kiss on top.
Return to oven and bake for 2 to 3 minutes more.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Cook meats.
Drain and season with pepper (no salt).
Melt cheese and combine with soup and Ro-Tel.
Add to meat and simmer until dip thickens.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Wonderful with shrimp, chicken or beef.
Marinade at least 2 hours or overnight!

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. Cream together the butter, sugar and egg. Add dry mixture, alternately with milk (add more milk, if necessary). Add the wild blueberries.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch well-greased Pyrex baking dish.
Top with Streusel. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk. Beat until thickened. Add sour cream and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and add lemon juice and vanilla. Last, layer vanilla wafers, banana slices and pudding mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Makes a big dish.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: In frying pan, brown sausage and drain.
Wash rice and add to the sausage.
Add soups and seasonings.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour in a casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato dish
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Add topping.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine cooked chicken, soup and sour cream in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with butter and poppy seed.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serve over hot rice.

title: uncle mikie's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Add additional milk in small amounts if necessary to thin batter.
Lightly oil a nonstick griddle with vegetable spray and heat it over medium heat.
On the heated griddle, pour sufficient amount of batter to make size of pancake desired.
Cook pancakes until they begin to bubble on the surface, then flip them over and lightly brown them on the other side.
Repeat the procedure until all the batter is used up, re-oiling the griddle only to prevent the pancakes from sticking to it.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put through food chopper.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Boil 1 pint vinegar, 1 pint water, 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 tablespoon salt.
Put mixture in peppers and boil all together for 5 to 10 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna in boiling water with 1 tablespoon of oil for 8 to 10 minutes. Rinse in cold water.

title: grape juice jelly
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add sugar.
Return to heat and cook 5 minutes.
Pour into jars.
This will keep for months.
This is very good with turkey instead of cranberries.

title: cinnamon apple crown(diet)
directions: Combine gelatin and hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart mold or mixing bowl. Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving plate.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add salt, pepper, paprika and flour, a little at a time.
Roll thin.
Cut and bake in moderate oven for 15 or 20 minutes.
For extra goodness, add 1/2 to 1 cup chopped pecans.
Top each biscuit with pecan half before baking.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Pour 1 can of chicken broth and half of water into a large pan. Add 1 pkg. of broccoli and cook until tender. Do the same with the other broth and broccoli. In a large bowl, blend milk and cornstarch with whisk. Microwave 5 minutes, whisking half way through. Whisk 1 cup

of flour into milk mixture until well blended. In a glass dish, microwave cheese for 2-3 minutes until soft. Pour half of the milk mixture and half of the cheese into each pan with broccoli. Cover and cook over low heat until thick, stirring often to prevent scorching. Serve immediately or when cooled, divide into serving-sized containers and freeze.

title: scalloped pineapple stuffing
directions: Drain pineapple.
Set aside.
Combine cubed bread, sugar, eggs and margarine.
Mix well.
Add milk and pineapple.
Spread ingredients in a 2-quart, greased baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve as a side dish with baked chicken.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; let cool.
Add cream cheese, sugar and sour cream; beat well.
Pour over graham cracker crust.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten each chicken breast; spread the breasts on a sheet of plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Cover with a second sheet.
Using a mallet or edge of a saucer, pound each breast until flat (1/4-inch thick).
Do not pound too hard or the chicken breasts will tear. Sprinkle one side of cutlets with salt and pepper.
Top each with a slice of ham.
Cut cheese into 4 bars.
Place a bar of cheese at one short end of each ham slice.
Fold long edges of cutlet over ends of bar of cheese.
Then starting at short end of cutlet, roll up, jelly-roll style.
To hold each chicken roll together, fasten with a wooden toothpick.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix as any other cake.	Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, oleo, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in 3 cups tart apples and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour in tube or sheet pan.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Last, add 1 cup boiling water.
Mix well again.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy blueberry cake
directions: Whip cream cheese with milk.
Layer blueberries, cheese and Dream Whip between cake layers.
Frost with Dream Whip.
Dribble blueberries over top.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: salada(rich and charlie's recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss before serving.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown 1 pound of sausage for each loaf of bread.
Saute onions and peppers until tender.
Let bread rise on well-greased cookie sheet.
Roll out flat when risen.
Spread sausage, onions and pepper on top.
You may add pepperoni.
Top with mushrooms, sliced olives and cheese.
Roll into a jelly roll, overlapping seams.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down, and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute the onion, green pepper, celery and garlic until tender. Add tomatoes, butter, chicken broth and all of the ingredients, except shrimp, oysters and rice, cooking on low heat for about 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and oysters.
Let cook for 3 to 5 minutes. Cook rice separately.
Pour gumbo over rice.

title: sarah's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients and put into a 2-quart casserole baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until bubbly.
You may also add water chestnuts if you like them.
This makes 8 to 10 servings.
Very good.

title: microwave fudge
directions: A good laugh is better than medicine.
When you laugh, you free your brain and release tension.
Laugh heartily in order to exercise unused muscles.
Laughter gives buoyancy to your spirit. It is a sound tonic. Learn to smile.
Smiles remove wrinkles and adds sparkle to the eyes.
Learn to be cheerful; tell a helpful story and that is the recipe for learning to laugh.

title: rosemary forcaccia bread
directions: Mix yeast and warm water in bowl; let set for 5 to 10 minutes in warm spot until it starts working.
Add remaining ingredients. With dough hook, mix at medium speed for 3 to 5 minutes, then low speed for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and shortening to form crumbs.
In a separate bowl, beat egg until fluffy.
Add molasses, boiling water and baking soda.
Beat until soda dissolves.
Reserve 1/4 cup of crumb mixture.
Stir remaining crumb mixture into molasses mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into pie crust; sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook macaroni for about 10 minutes.
Mix all the ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add water if needed.

title: italian sausage and green peppers
directions: Brown sausage pieces; pour off all but 3 tablespoons of grease.
Reserve sausages.
Saute onions and peppers in grease until peppers are bright green.
Add remaining ingredients and sausage pieces.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream the softened butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients with flour.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately. Add vanilla; mix well.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 7 or 8 dozen cookies.

title: cool 'n easy watermelon pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove remaining ice. Stir in Cool Whip until smooth. Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours until firm.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick, put in bottom of baking dish, cover with apples and marshmallows.
Stir sugar, salt and cinnamon together; sprinkle over potatoes.
Mix cornstarch and water together and pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: casserole alaska
directions: Butter 4 slices bread, cut or break into cubes.
Flake salmon, combine with bread in buttered casserole.
Beat egg slightly. Pour over bread and salmon and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: pizza buns
directions: Brown beef, onion and seasonings.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add cubed cheese and olives.
Spread on hot dog or hamburger buns and wrap in foil.
Heat at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be frozen before baking and served as a snack or picnic item.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine the sugars and sour cream in a large saucepan and cook slowly until sugars are dissolved.
Cook until a little of the mixture dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla and cool to 145° or until the outside of the saucepan feels warm to the touch.
Beat until quite stiff, then add enough cream while beating to make of a spreading consistency.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Blend soda, salt and flour together.
Sift 2 times and add sour cream.
Alternate with flour.
Preheat oven at 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tests done.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Place ground beef in a large bowl.
Add salt, pepper, onion, tomato paste, eggs and flour.
Mix ingredients well.
Hull out insides of bell peppers (seeds and pulpy matter), leaving bottom intact.
Stuff meat mixture into bell peppers.
Place stuffed peppers in roasting pan; cover bottom of pan with water.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: macaroons
directions: In large bowl combine coconut, milk, and flour until well blended. Drop by rounded tablespoons about 2 inches a part. Bake at 350 for 8- 10 minutes off until edges are golden. Cool on baking sheet 2 -3 minutes. May add 12 oz. of M&M semi sweet chocolate mini baking bits to mix Or regular size M&M on top of cookies before baking.

title: pudding cake
directions: Make pudding according to recipe on box.
Put down in bottom of 8 1/2 x 12 1/2 x 2-inch rectangular cake pan (approximately) one layer of graham crackers.
Follow this by 1/2 of the pudding followed by another layer of graham crackers and remainder of pudding.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top.
Mix icing with small amount of milk and spread on top layer of graham crackers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Prepare night before in order for crackers to be soft when served.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix and pour into pan over unbaked cake mixture.

title: fried chicken
directions: Melt in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 375° oven the vegetable oil and margarine.
In airtight bag, mix the flour, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic salt. Dip chicken in oil, then shake in bag (no more than 3 pieces at a time).
Place skin side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan with oil and melted margarine.
Bake 45 minutes. Turn over and bake 15 minutes longer.
(For crispier coating, cook longer.)

title: avocado dip
directions: Beat avocados, onions, lemon juice, salt, pepper and picante sauce until creamy.
Stir in tomato.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.
(I use a food processor or blender.
Use picante sauce until the right consistency for dip is achieved.)
Serve with corn chips.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Crush Oreos until it looks like dirt in a food processor.
Set aside.
Mix pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Stir pudding until it starts to set; set aside.
In another bowl, mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter until creamy.
Take Cool Whip and fold into pudding mixture.
Layer in flowerpot in the following order: dirt, pudding, dirt, cream cheese, dirt, pudding, dirt.

title: scallop's veronique
directions: Saute onions in butter over medium heat until tender.
Add scallops.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and sherry in a cup.
Add to scallop mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Stir in mayonnaise, mushrooms, grapes and pepper.
Spoon mixture into 4 individual ovenproof dishes. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Broil 5 inches from heat, 2 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix by hand until moistened.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes (8 minutes for soft cookies or 12 minutes for crisp cookies).
Remove immediately from sheet and cool.
Flatten as you drop on sheet for a "tea cake."

title: matt's favorite white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add eggs plus yolks, one at a time. Beat until smooth. Add cream. Switch to whisk and add chocolate. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; drop to 250° until set.

title: candied sweet potatoes with apples
directions: "Home Week" as	set
aside by Penn School, the 4th week of October so	that
children	could
work
at home with their parents to work in the house and garden.

title: stuffed green cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage and cut out about an inch of the core, leaving enough so leaves stay together.
Cook whole cabbage 5 minutes, covered in boiling salted water.
Drain and cool.
When cool enough to handle, turn back leaves.
Saute sausage, ground beef and onion until lightly browned.
Mix with rice and egg.
When cool insert by spoonfuls between cabbage leaves.
When all meat mixture has been used, place cabbage in large pot.
Mix tomatoes and sage and pour around cabbage.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove cabbage to serving platter.
Mix yogurt with tomatoes and pour over cabbage. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Trim fat from chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Brown in oil along with garlic buds, onion, mushrooms and spices.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer until cooked thoroughly.
Cook spaghetti, according to directions.
Add sauce.
(I freeze leftovers in small individual servings.)
When frozen, defrost in microwave and warm.

title: prune cake
directions: Place sugar, eggs and oil in large bowl and mix with electric beater.
Add alternatively flour, buttermilk, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, cloves and soda.
Mix well.
Add prunes, nuts and raisins. Mix well.
Pour batter into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Freezes well.
Serve with Cool Whip, whipping cream or 4x sugar sprinkled on top.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Press firmly with a fork into bottom of dish to make crust.
Pour cherry pie filling on top of crust.
Cream together the sugar and cream cheese, then fold in the Cool Whip.
Spoon this on top of the cherry filling. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Roll in the chipped beef.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt and stir in.
Add nuts and mix well.
Chill dough for at least 30 minutes; roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar, then roll in powdered sugar again.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: choice rolls
directions: Melt shortening into hot milk, then cool.
Dissolve yeast into the warm water.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Dough may be sticky, but do not add more flour.
Let rise, roll out and cut. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chicken in the oil and transfer to an oven casserole.
Add tomatoes and their liquid.
Add rice. Lower temperature to 325°.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Fluff rice; add the defrosted peas and arrange pimentos on top.
Cook, covered, an additional 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: 6 beans sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage with onions.
Drain.
Mix beans.
Add to mixture of beans and sausage the tomato soup, mustard and brown sugar. Mix tomato paste with a little water and spread on top of bean mixture. Lay strips of bacon on top.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 375° for 1 hour.

title: animal cracker necklaces
directions: Melt candy coating over low heat.
Spread candy coating on flat side of 4 animal crackers.
Place 1 pretzel in the coating on each cracker, leaving top two holes of pretzel open for threading cord of necklace.
Allow to set.
Repeat with remaining crackers and pretzels.
Put cord through pretzels/crackers, alternate with ring-shaped candy and/or cereal.
Makes 8 necklaces.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake at 275° for 4 1/2 hours (covered).

title: malted milk date bars
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Melt oleo in a medium saucepan; add brown sugar.
Stir in vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients slowly.
Add dates and pecans with last of flour and mix thoroughly.
Bake in well-greased and floured square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares or bars.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Rinse and drain oysters.
Layer bottom of baking dish with crumbs then add layer of oysters. Dot with butter and sprinkle on celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Repeat until dish is filled. Cover top layer with crumbs and dot with remaining butter. Pour milk over top, using fork to allow milk to soak down evenly.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order given in large salad bowl. Combine mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar. Spread over cheese layer. Chill. Sprinkle bacon bits over top before serving.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and eggs on low speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Add mashed bananas and mix well. Add cake mix and blend well. Divide between 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on rack before slicing. Freezes well.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan over medium heat.
Add sausage and cook 5 minutes.
Add chicken, sear on both sides and remove mixture to plate.
Add onion and celery to pan and cook 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook 1 minute.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid and add to pan.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Stir in rice, oregano, pepper, thyme and cayenne.
Measure reserved tomato juice and add enough broth to equal 2 cups.
Add liquid, chicken and sausage mixture.
Add 2nd can of tomatoes.
Bring to boil, lower heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add okra.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: boy scout omelet
directions: You also need quart size Ziploc bag.

title: hot dogs and beans
directions: Cut hot dogs in bite-size pieces.
Chop onion and cook until hot dogs are browned.
Add can of baked beans and simmer.
Add a dash of black pepper and a dash or two of chili pepper.
Add A.1. sauce (about 1/4 cup) and cover and cook on low heat about 10 minutes or until hot.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt together.
Add boiling water, while stirring constantly, using high heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Then cook slowly on low heat until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 2 minutes longer on low heat.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour into a previously baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Let cool slightly.
Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Add milk and then add other ingredients.
Use lemon juice on apples and bananas to keep from turning dark.

title: wednesday night chicken pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into a greased Pyrex dish (9 x 11-inch).
Top with a pie crust made of the milk and Bisquick. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until nicely brown.
The crust will be thin.
When crust begins to brown, brush with melted butter.

title: italian omelet peasant style
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and brown in oil over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Reduce heat.
Pour eggs on sausage and cook until eggs are thick and creamy.
Serve very hot.
Serves 4.

title: creamed white onions
directions: Pour onions into medium saucepan.
Cover and simmer over low heat until warm through.
Drain.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cover until melted.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Return to low heat.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat until warm, stirring gently often.
Mix cornstarch and water.
While stirring onions, add cornstarch mixture.
Stir gently until sauce thickens.
Serve immediately.

title: candied cucumbers
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water for 7 to 8 days.
Take out and rinse good.
Cut cucumbers in slices and soak in alum and water to cover for 1 day.
Take out and rinse good.
Soak in apple cider vinegar for 1 day.
Take cucumbers out and pour vinegar down drain.
Use stone or glass jar and layer cucumbers with sugar. Stir once in awhile.
Do not seal during soaking.
You may leave cucumbers and syrup in the stone or glass jar or store in smaller jars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts without skins on.
After done, save 2 cups of the broth and add butter; set aside.
Take the chicken off the bone and put it in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken and cream of celery soups together; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle seasoning mix over the sour cream mixture. Last, pour broth or melted butter over seasoning mix.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Add more water if necessary.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine vegetables, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper. Combine vinegar, mustard and salad dressing.
Add to vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Makes 3 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: In a small frying pan, melt butter.
Saute onion and add thawed and very well drained spinach to the onion.
Cut cream cheese up and add to spinach.
Stir until cheese melts.
Mix egg slightly and add to spinach.
Add bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add chicken bouillon; mix well.
Put mixture into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
You may sprinkle on more bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese before cooking if you wish. Serves 4.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal and 2 cups milk in a saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until consistency of mush. Remove from heat; add salt, baking powder, oil and 1 cup milk. Beat egg yolks and stir into cornmeal mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: mud cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk, and butter together for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Mix well and
drop on wax paper.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Cook peas and salt pork about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa and sugar in large mixer bowl; mix well. Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add eggs, vanilla and water; beat well.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until layers test done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Spread frosting between layers and over top and side of cake.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer at
least 15 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour over apple mixture in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
This may be doubled in 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Scant sugar when doubling and bake a little longer.)

title: easy chicken gumbo
directions: Melt margarine.
Add okra, onion and green bell pepper.
Saute until tender.
Stir in broth, tomatoes, bay leaf, allspice, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; stir in rice, cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken and cook just until thoroughly heated.
Remove bay leaf and allspice.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water.
Drain.
Add oregano to spaghetti sauce.
Grease baking dish; make layers in order, half each, noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: pork and veal casserole
directions: Cut meat in 3/4-inch cubes and brown with onion and simmer until done.
Add chicken broth and simmer a little longer.
Boil noodles about 10 minutes.
Add noodles, cheese, pepper, mushrooms, corn and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a buttered casserole and cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli bake
directions: In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain liquid from 1 jar artichokes into 1-quart saucepan. Drain liquid from second jar and discard.
Finely chop all artichokes.
Set aside. Grease 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In liquid in saucepan, over medium heat, cook minced onion until tender.

In medium bowl, with fork, beat eggs until blended. Stir in cooked onion, chopped artichokes, cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper. Spread mixture evenly in baking dish (if not baking right away, cover and refrigerate).
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake mixture 30 to 35 minutes until set and lightly browned. Cool 15 minutes in dish on wire rack.
Cut into 4 strips, lengthwise, then cut each strip into 6 pieces.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Lightly grease Bundt pan or tube pan.
Sprinkle bottom with pecans and place frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle the dry pudding over rolls.
Melt butter (margarine); add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put this mixture over the frozen rolls.
Let rise overnight (uncovered) at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white jello
directions: Mix 8 oz. cream cheese, sugar, vanilla. Add milk, gelatin, water and mix. Add cool whip and mix. Chill.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Peel and quarter lengthwise the zucchini; cut crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add zucchini and garlic until brown.
Add tomatoes and thyme.
Simmer until everything is warm.
Season to taste.

title: corn crisped chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into evaporated milk.
Then roll in mixture of cornflake crumbs, Accent, salt and pepper.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan lined with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until drumstick is tender.

title: salsa
directions: Cook to boil for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 pints.

title: gail's fettucini
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and celery in butter.
Add parsley, garlic and crawfish.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add flour, cream and cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil and drain noodles.
Add to mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: veggy pizza
directions: In an 11 x 15-inch greased pan, unroll crescent rolls.
Pinch together and form edge and pat in place.
Bake for 11 minutes at 375°.
Mix together cream cheese, Miracle Whip, dill weed, Accent and garlic powder.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle veggies and top with grated cheeses.

title: old fashioned cream corn
directions: Shuck and silk corn.
Cut corn off cob and scrape cob.
Place water and sugar in large saucepan.
Add corn and simmer for 20 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: old fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Using mixer, cream butter and sugar until butter and sugar are softened and mixture is light. Add all ingredients and combine, mixing well. Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 to 50 minutes until center is set. Allow pie to cool completely before serving. Serve pie with fresh strawberries or slices of peaches, if desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: moon cake
directions: Beat egg whites in small bowl; fold in 2 tablespoons regular flour.
Set mixture aside.
In large bowl, add sugar, egg yolks and dry ingredients.
Alternate with milk.
Fold egg white mixture into large bowl.
Pour batter into greased jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Sprinkle with nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool, then cut with donut cutter into crescent shapes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding over crushed pineapple.
Then add marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix and let set for a few hours.
Green coloring may be added to make salad more colorful.

title: shrimp romalade
directions: Let mixture stand 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over shredded lettuce.

title: indian country casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix all other ingredients well and pour into baking dish. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° until rice is tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and chill.
Form into a ball and roll in crushed nuts.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add
flour, seasonings and mix.
Then add water and bring to boil.
Simmer at least 30 minutes;
Add tomatoes and beans as desired.
Heat to simmer. Serve with corn chips and shredded cheddar cheese.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cover with foil if it gets too brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
You may use Velveeta or Old English cheese on top.
Serves 12 generously.

title: fried onion rings
directions: In a bowl combine flour, milk, egg, the 1 tablespoon oil and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Beat with a rotary beater just until smooth.

title: corn broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish. Cover the top with extra bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat bottom and sides of 2-quart baking dish with 1 tablespoon butter.
Melt remaining butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onions, cook over moderate heat for 3 minutes.
Do not let onions brown.
Remove from heat, stir in flour to a smooth paste.
Add milk and beat to dissolve flour.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth and thick.
Remove from heat, beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in tomato paste, tuna, lemon juice, salt and cayenne.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff enough to form peaks.
Stir tablespoon of whites into tuna mixture.
Fold in remaining whites.
Pour into dish. Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: fudge "skillet" cake
directions: Spoon topping evenly over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
To remove from skillet, loosen cake and icing from sides if necessary and turn out onto serving plate.
Scrape remaining icing from skillet.
Spread on cake.
Serve with ice cream.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and chill for several hours. Serve with raw vegetables or potato chips.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins, water, cinnamon, sugar and shortening.
Cool. Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: In large bowl, toss together salad leaves, strawberries and almonds.

title: victor's lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings (except caraway).
Cook noodles until tender.
Lightly spray glass baking dish (9 x 13-inches) with Pam.
Put 4 noodles in baking dish.
Add 1/3 meat sauce.
Add 1/3 cup cottage cheese and 1/3 pound Mozzarella (sprinkled).

title: ham mustard sauce
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar in jar, let set overnight.
Next morning in top of double boiler, place egg, beat in sugar, dash salt and dry mustard and vinegar mixture.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve with baked ham.

title: everyday cupcakes(makes 15)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix shortening and sugar.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add egg and half of milk. Mix until flour is moist. Beat at low, adding remaining milk and vanilla.
Fill cupcake cups 1/2 way.
Bake for 20 minutes. Cool, then frost.

title: chicken stew with dumplings
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in a medium size baking dish, thicker pieces facing toward the outer edge of dish.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered with waxed paper, in microwave at power level "High" for 19 to 20 minutes.
Drain off all liquid.
Combine soup and 2/3 cup milk and pour over chicken.
Cover and microwave for 6 minutes, stirring once.

title: miniature cheese cups
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Spoon some graham cracker crust mixture on bottom of miniature paper cups.
Press down with bottom of a shot glass.
Put 1 good tablespoon of cream cheese mixture in cup, but don't fill to top. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 44 cups.

title: 7 layer cookie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine and pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle one cup of coconut over top of crust.
Add peanut butter or butterscotch chips over top of coconut.
Add chocolate chips over top of other chips.
Add 1 cup pecan nuts over chips.
Pour can of Eagle Brand milk over all. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mom's divinity candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until syrup spins a long thread when dropped from a fork.
Add 2/3 of the syrup to beaten egg whites; return rest of syrup to burner and bring to a full boil. Add to mixture and beat until it loses its gloss and is creamy. Add vanilla and nuts.
Put on 2 meat platters.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when the mixture reaches a full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add oats and vanilla.
Add other ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: eggs la strada
directions: Remove crust from bread and quarter.
Put 6 slices in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer diced ham over bread, then layer shredded cheese over ham.
Put the other 6 slices of bread over layers. Mix milk, eggs, salt and mustard together. Pour over layers. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: fast fixin' chocolate, chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Pour
oil into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.	Put remaining ingredients into pan and stir with fork or spoon until blended (about 2
minutes).
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted
near
center
comes
out	clean.	Cooled cake may be sprinkled
with
powdered
sugar.
Store cake loosely covered. Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: chicken picatta(serves 1)
directions: Dissolve chicken soup in water and pour into frying pan.
Add lemon juice, garlic powder and chicken.
Saute each side for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove chicken to warm plate and cover. Place mushrooms in frying pan; add water and garlic powder.
Saute for about 4 minutes, then pour over chicken and serve.

title: moms eggnog
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer until smooth.

title: amber cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar and mix thoroughly. Spread mix into lightly greased 10 x 15 x 1/2-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes at 275°.
Remove from oven.
Use a teaspoon to scoop out cookies.
Form into balls with fingers. Be careful, it is hot.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken with 2 bay leaves and celery until tender.
Bone chicken (break into pieces) and place in oblong glass baking dish. Fold soup and cream together.
Add to chicken.
Mix margarine and crumbs and put on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium saucepan, melt butterscotch chips and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs; mix well.
Reserve 2/3 cup of crumb mixture. Press remainder firmly into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: blt pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions and drain.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, chili sauce, ReaLemon, bouillon, and sugar; stir macaroni, tomato, and onions.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in lettuce and bacon.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: libby's pasta shrimp salad
directions: Prepare pasta per directions; rinse in cold water and drain completely.
Add all other ingredients, except dressing.
Add dressing just before serving; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix
flour,
salt,
baking
powder, sugar and cinnamon. Add egg, milk and butter.
Add apples.	Pour in greased muffin tins. Sprinkle
top
with
sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: slushy fruit punch
directions: Heat together 6 cups water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Cool; mix together cooled sugar syrup and add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice and bananas.
Freeze. About 3 hours before ready to use, set out of freezer.
Let thaw until slushy.
Add ginger ale at time of serving.
Makes about 30 cups.
Can be kept sealed in freezer for 1 to 2 months.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Fry bacon; crumble and set aside.
In same frying pan, saute onion and jalapeno pepper.
Mash peas well or place in food processor.
Add sauteed onion and pepper mixture, including drippings.
Add crumbled bacon and Cheez Whiz.
Blend well.
Serve hot with chips.

title: golden oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Melt butter with garlic clove in shallow baking pan.
Dip chicken pieces in garlic butter and then in crumb mixture.
Place in baking pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes. Baste occasionally with pan drippings.
Do not turn pieces.

title: custard sauce
directions: Heat milk in top of double boiler over direct heat until tiny bubbles appear around edge of pan.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt to mix well.
Very slowly, pour hot milk into egg mixture, beating constantly.
Return mixture to double boiler top; place over hot, not boiling, water.
(Water in lower part of double boiler should not touch upper part.)
Cook, stirring constantly, until this coating forms on metal spoon, approximately 8 to 10 minutes. Immediately pour custard into a bowl; place sheet of waxed paper directly on surface.
Set bowl in cold water to cool.
Stir in lemon peel.
Refrigerate until very cold, several hours or overnight.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: gilge pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Place egg yolk in a cup and fill it up
with
milk
to
make 2/3 cup.
Work out on floured counter. Makes 2 double crusts.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except bread) in bowl.
Cut ring around top of loaf and remove bread inside, leaving about 1 inch around the loaf.
Fill with dip mixture; replace the round top. Wrap in foil and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Break the bread into pieces and toast.
Serve with dip, also raw vegetables.

title: veggie chicken pockets
directions: Prepare dressing mix.
Carefully cut chicken breasts off bones in one piece, leaving skin on.
Slowly separate skin from thickest part of breast with your fingers, leaving skin attached at edges.

title: buttermilk custard pie
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mix the sour cream, soup, milk, parsley and 1 cup of the cheese together.
Salt and pepper ham and potatoes.
Add to the sour cream mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook bacon and put aside.
Drain grease from pan; saute onion and bell or hot peppers.
Add eggs, scrambled, to pan.
Crumble bacon in also.
When almost done, add cheese on top.
Spoon into tortillas; add hot sauce, if desired.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots for 30 minutes in warm water.
Drain and cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in water and orange juice.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Blend in chopped nuts and apricots.
Pour into greased pan, 9 1/2 x 5 x 2 3/4-inches.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350° or until wooden toothpick thrust into center comes out clean.
Remove from pan. Let cool on rack.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, margarine, salt and pepper and press into 8 x 12 pan.
Bake at 400 until golden brown.
I do this the day before and store in refrigerator.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into cooked hash brown crust.
Bake until eggs are set, about 20 minutes, in 375 degree oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put into a bowl and mix.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy creamy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Put undrained broccoli in blender.
In small saucepan, heat milk and butter (do not boil). Stir in potato flakes and onion. Add milk mixture to broccoli and process briefly.
Return to saucepan. Add broth and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
For thinner consistency, add a little more milk.
Makes 6 half cup servings.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef (drain).
Add garlic powder, onion, salt, oregano and tomato sauce and paste.
Cook until thick, about 5 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
In 2-quart casserole dish, layer noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, tomato mix and Parmesan cheese.
Make 3 layers like the list.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: apple crisp(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Thoroughly grease Dutch oven.
In a large bowl, work together the butter, sugar and flour until crumbly.
In medium bowl, mix together the cinnamon and flour.
Slice each apple into 12 or 16 slices.
Remove seeds, but leave peel on.
Fill Dutch oven with apples.
Add mixture of cinnamon and water.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with nondairy whipped topping.
Serves 12.

title: christmas candy cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 250 degrees. Grease and flour a 9-inch springform pan with the tube insert. Combine the cherries, pineapple, dates and flour in a large bowl.
Toss to coat the fruit with the flour.
Add the pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Add the condensed milk. Mix well. Press into prepared pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Wrap tightly in foil.
It will keep, refrigerated, for several weeks.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Tips (For Blueberry Dessert):
Substitute blueberry pie filling for the cherry filling.

title: zucchini custard casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion together until tender.
Drain out all juices. In same kettle return drained zucchini and stir in cheese, margarine, crumbled crackers and eggs.
Add milk until it looks like heavy paste.
Pour into greased casserole or pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Good served hot or cold or warmed over.
Will freeze.

title: no fat banana cake
directions: Combine banana, applesauce and egg whites.
Mix with mixer until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan (sprayed with Pam). Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pecan crispy cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peaches and cream cobbler
directions: Mix together pudding mix, flour, milk, egg and margarine.
Beat for 2 minutes and spread in bottom of flat 2-quart pan which has been coated with vegetable spray.
Drain peaches and spread over dough mixture.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and reserved peach juice.
Beat for 2 minutes and spread over peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chilled cheese cake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Fold in whipped cream and pour into crumb crust.
Chill several hours.
Clean strawberries and place in a ring on top of chilled pie.
Brush strawberries with melted jelly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Press into baking dish and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Prepare jello by dissolving in 2 cups boiling water and then adding 1 cup cold water.
Stir in frozen strawberries.
Let set.
Cream sugar with cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust and then add strawberry jello. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and potatoes.
Sift in dry ingredients
and mix alternately with buttermilk and vanilla, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased cake pans and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: cauliflower casserole with shell pasta
directions: Put cauliflower in a 2-quart gratin dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter and add flour.
Cook roux mixture over low heat for 3 minutes, stirring often, but don't brown it.
Heat milk to scalding separately.
This can be done in the microwave 4 to 5 minutes on High.
Pour the hot milk all at once into the roux, stirring constantly over medium heat until sauce is bubbling.
Add the seasonings and Parmesan cheese; whisk until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in Mozzarella.
Combine shells with cauliflower.
Pour sauce over mixture.
Gently work the stringy cheese into the cauliflower and shells.
Top casserole with seasoned bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until browned.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first three ingredients and set aside.
Next, mix cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Add your jello and blend well. Pour into mold and refrigerate, covered.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: peanut butter sandwich
directions: Put a little bit of jelly on one slice of bread and just enough peanut butter on the other slice of bread.
Put both slices together and one tasty, real yummy peanut butter sandwich.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add peanut butter, creaming well. Add unbeaten eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Shape by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a chocolate star on top of each cookie, pressing down so that cookie cracks around the edge. Return to oven; bake 3 to 4 minutes longer.

title: quick and easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off any excess fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: layer tortilla pie
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add olives, if desired.
Mix well and simmer for 5 minutes.
Lightly butter tortillas on one side only.
Place on tortilla, buttered side down, in a 2-quart round casserole.
Spoon about 1/2 cup of meat mixture on the tortilla, then sprinkle about 1/3 cup cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Pour water around the sides of casserole (not over the top).
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with shredded lettuce and sour cream, if desired.

title: quick nachos(just 4 ingredients!)
directions: Layer on platter.
Micro cook on 100% power a couple of minutes until cheese is melted, turning platter once.
Makes 20 servings.
50 calories per serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a Pyrex dish.
Mix together celery soup, chicken broth and margarine.
Pour over chicken.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Brown beef with taco mix.
Place all ingredients in a square glass dish.
Spread layer of refried beans to cover bottom of dish.
Then repeat process with each additional layer.
Serve with Doritos or Mexican chips.

title: baked string beans
directions: Put cracker crumbs on top and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Mix vanilla, eggs, salt, evaporated milk and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Pour 1/2 cup flour over the chopped walnuts and cherries that have been cut in half. Mix and spoon into batter.
Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured or sprayed with Pam.
Bake in cold oven set at 300° for 2 1/4 hours.

title: cracker spread
directions: Divide cream cheese in half and spread onto 2 plates.
Evenly distribute the sauce over each plate of cream cheese. Sprinkle the crab meat evenly over the sauce on each plate.
Spread with knife onto crackers of your choice.

title: english pizza
directions: Baking time: 5 to 10 minutes.
Temperature: 400°.
Size pan: cookie sheet.

title: george's rice
directions: Drain mushrooms and add to rice. Combine sherry, butter and mushroom juice to make 1 cup. Put into baking dish. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into balls. Mix soup and water in pot of a pressure cooker.
Drop meatballs into pressure cooker.
Cover; set control at 10 and cook 10 minutes after control jiggles.
Cool cooker normally for 5 minutes, then place under faucet.
Serves 4. This recipe is both fast and very popular with children!

title: chess pie
directions: Put sugah, flour 'n cornmeal in a bowl 'n toss litely wid a fork...now drap in the aigs, 'n everthang else...beat til smooth 'n blended reel gud...pore in an unbaked 9-inch pie shell 'n bake at 375° fur 'bout 45 minutes til a golden brown.
WOW!

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Butter 4 slices of bread and place them in a lightly greased 12-inch pan. In a medium mixing bowl, mix together vanilla, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and milk. Pour over bread and let set for 10 to 15 minutes. In a small bowl, mix together cinnamon and 1/3 c. sugar; sprinkle over bread. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in small amount of oil.
Cook slowly until meat turns white.
Drain off fat.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dolores' harvest zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini, remove stem and blossom end but do not peel. Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
In large skillet, cook and stir zucchini and onion in butter until butter is melted.
Cover, cook, stirring occasionally until zucchini is tender-crisp.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Gently stir into zucchini and heat through. Serves 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs on low speed.
Then mix flour, cinnamon and nutmeg to mixture by hand.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla to mixture.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Pour mixture in and bake at 325° for 70 to 75 minutes.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Rinse chicken in cold water and pat dry in clean cloth. Mix biscuit mix, salt and paprika in paper bag and shake chicken in mixture until covered.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Quickly brown pork chops.
In a large greased casserole dish, add a layer of pork chops, then a layer of sliced potatoes. Repeat layers, adding salt and pepper to each.
Mix mushroom soup and water.
Pour over potatoes and meat.
Bake, covered, with glass lid at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour or until potatoes are done.

title: plum cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: carnival dessert
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar and add milk alternately with flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sour cherries.
Add nuts. Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan for 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: curried cauliflower casserole
directions: In medium bowl, stir together soup, cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder until well blended.
Place cauliflower in 2-quart casserole; pour sauce over cauliflower.
In small bowl, mix together bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: luncheon roll
directions: Wrap chicken around 2 or 3 of the spears, wrap ham around that.
Then put this on a slice of buttered bread and roll like a jelly roll. Put as many servings as you would like in deep dish and pour melted butter over.
Bake until bread is brown.
Serve cheese sauce over it.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Mix together cocoa, coconut, raisins, cornflakes, nuts, fruit juice, wafer crumbs and milk.
Blend well.
Lightly spray a 7-inch square baking dish with nonstick cooking spray and line with foil. Spray foil.
Press mixture lightly and evenly into bottom of dish.
Pour melted chocolate over mixture, spreading smooth.
Let stand a few minutes.
Score lines with a knife.
Chill until firm. Cut along score lines.

title: the best beef stew
directions: Add to meat mixture and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: toasty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
