Place peaches in square baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of peaches. Bake about 30 minutes or until peaches are tender.

title: grandma bonnie's cornmeal pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal in large bowl. Add eggs, melted butter and milk. Beat with mixer until smooth. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for about 40 minutes.

title: mom's sicilian chicken cacciatore
directions: Clean chicken and pat dry.
Chop onions and celery.
Halve olives
by hitting each one with a flat bottomed glass or bottle. Cover bottom of a large stock pot with olive oil.
Fry small batches of chicken, seasoning each batch well with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Remove to platter.
When last batch of chicken is done, remove from pot and add onions and celery.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Add olives, capers and chicken along with cooking juices of chicken and simmer.
To prevent chicken from breaking up in pot cover and, while holding cover down, remove from stove top and shake entire pot instead of stirring. If more juice is desired, add 1 cup of water.
Let simmer at least 1 1/2 hours.
Add vinegar 1/2 hour before done.
Serve with a green lettuce salad and lots of Italian bread.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Crumble cake into bite size pieces. Mix together Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip, lemon juice and strawberries.
Pour over cake pieces; mix well and pour into large cake pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chess cake lemon
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan the first three ingredients.
Beat and pour over crust the last four ingredients. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 300°.
Cut into squares.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and 3/4 cup melted margarine in bowl. Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread softened ice cream over cookie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Bring chocolate syrup, margarine and condensed milk to a boil in saucepan, stirring frequently.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over ice cream layer; sprinkle with pecans.
Freeze until serving time. Yields 12 servings.

title: christmas brownie bars
directions: Place
chocolate
and
butter in top of a double boiler, melt over medium heat until completely melted.
Beat eggs with wire whisk
only
to mix, not foamy.
Add vanilla and sugar and beat to mix
only.
Add
melted
chocolate and stir with whisk until chocolate
is incorporated.
With a spatula, fold in the flour and then
diced
fruit.
Pour on top of cookie base that has been cooked.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Bake the night before or two days before, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: stuffed meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Pack 1/2 of mixture lightly in a 2-quart glass loaf pan.
Make a depression into center.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Press in pie plate and chill.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: I was walking down life's highway, a long time ago.
One day I saw a sign that read "HEAVEN'S GROCERY STORE".
As I got a little closer the door came open wide, and when I came to myself, I was just inside.

title: fulton's holiday combination pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream the sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one. Add pineapple, coconut and pecans to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until firm.

title: barb's stuffed spinach shells
directions: Brown meat; add spinach.
Cook until completely thawed.
Grate about 1/2 of cheese into meat-spinach mixture.
Stir until cheese melts and mixture sticks together.
Cool.
Cook macaroni shells. Cool until they're comfortable to handle.
Stuff with meat mixture (about a tablespoon in each shell).
Place in baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with remainder of Brick cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt; work in the shortening until like coarse meal.
Sprinkle water over flour mixture until completely moistened.
Form into a ball.
Roll dough and fit into a 9-inch pie pan.
Prick pastry.
Bake in 375° oven for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
1 pie crust.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake until knife comes out clean.

title: le 'mont blanc' en surprise(snow mousse with a surprise; for 10 persons)
directions: Put the walnuts on a baking sheet in a moderate oven to warm, but not brown.
Put the sugar and 3 tablespoons of water into a saucepan; set over medium heat and boil to form a light caramel syrup.

Immediately add the warmed walnuts; stir over the heat for a few seconds to distribute the nuts through the caramel and being careful of the caramel, pour it onto an oiled baking sheet, spreading it out into an even layer with a spatula.
Set aside to cool and harden.
Chop into 1/8-inch pieces.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly together and pour into 1 well-greased and floured 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Double this recipe for use in turkey dressing.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel and cut up carrots.
Place in boiler with margarine, sugar, salt and water.
Boil on medium to high until liquid forms into a light, thin syrup.
Serves 10.

title: beans and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bell pepper and onion.
Mix beans, catsup, sugar and mustard.
Mix well with hamburger mixture.
Bake in large casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour and chill. Working with small amount of dough (keep remainder cold) roll out very thin and cut.
Brush with milk or egg and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Put nut in the center and bake quickly.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over batter.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: party potato chips
directions: Put on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: african dill dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with any salad.

title: snickernoodles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift together remaining ingredients and stir into mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned, but still soft.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: no cook cherry delight
directions: Pinch angel food cake in small pieces.
Place in oblong Pyrex dish.
In large bowl, add Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour over angel food cake pieces.
Top with red pie cherries.
Place in refrigerator overnight or until used.

title: apple pan eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Put butter and apple slices into a 9-inch Pyrex pie pan. Place in 425° oven for about 5 minutes to melt butter and soften apples. Beat flour and milk into eggs with a whisk, leaving batter slightly lumpy. Pour batter over butter and apples. Bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve immediately. Pass mixture of cinnamon and sugar or syrup, if desired.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add corn meal to boiling water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add margarine, sugar, baking powder, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Stiffly beat egg whites.
Bake in a 2-quart baking dish at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mushroom vegetable soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, carrots, celery, tomato, onion and garlic in butter and oil until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in beef broth, water, barley, thyme, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes. Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: pineapple oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon and press down on lightly-greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: makato's shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Combine all ingredients.
May be cooked in a skillet over medium heat or in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid has cooked down.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello and let partly jell.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mash and cream with mayonnaise.
Add carrots.
When jello is ready, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and carrots.
Add pineapple.
Pour into greased mold.

title: pancakes for one person
directions: Mix liquids slowly to flour and sugar, then bake on greased skillet or griddle.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt caramels in microwave.
Add cream cheese and mix well. Dip apples (on sticks) and place on wax paper.
Sauce may be used as a topping on ice cream or on apple pie.

title: cranberry baked beans
directions: Place rinsed beans, salt, juice and water in a heavy pan. Bring to a boil; remove from heat and set aside 1 hour.
Cover and re-boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, adding more water, if necessary.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Preheat oven to 250°. Combine beans with onion, molasses, ginger, mustard, catsup and brown sugar.
Place half of the beans in a bean pot or heavy casserole.
Top with half of the bacon.
Repeat layers.
Pour 1 1/2 cups reserved liquid over the top.
Bake, covered, 5 hours. Uncover and bake 1 hour longer.
Add more liquid during the baking time if beans seem too dry.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ellie's mississippi mud brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan. Add sugar and stir well.
Add eggs and cream well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes (done on edges, soft in middle).
Prepare frosting (recipe follows) while brownies are baking.

title: hot chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spread onto 6 slices bread.
Cover with remaining slices and place in baking dish.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Spread on sandwiches. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and bake until melted.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine pasta, shrimp, onions and parmesan cheese.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over pasta mixture and toss.
Cover and chill for 1-2 hours.

title: joe's scampi
directions: Wash, peel and devein shrimp.
Melt butter in medium skillet over low heat.
Add onions and garlic and saute until golden, about 8 minutes.
Add shrimp and stir until pink.
Add wine, lemon juice, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Excellent over angel hair pasta.
Serves 4 to 6. Yummy!

title: cabbage meal in one
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges and place in greased 3-quart casserole. Mix raw ground meat, rice and onion.
Arrange between wedges. Combine tomatoes, water and seasoning.
Pour over the casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Melt together cream cheese and milk.
Add other ingredients. Put noodles and mixture in layers in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add condensed milk, evaporated milk, vanilla, whipping cream and half and half. Mix.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill line on freezer.
Churn to freeze in freezer.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: 9-day cucumber pickles
directions: First Day:
2 cups salt and boiling water to cover and let cukes stand 24 hours; drain.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 medium muffin cups.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg. Stir in flour and nutmeg alternately with milk. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cinnamon. Immediately after baking, roll puffs in melted butter, then in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until coarse like meal. Add nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until lightly browned.
Soften cream cheese; beat in egg.
Add pumpkin, milk, spice and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in hot water.
Pour onto baked crust.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350° until filling is barely set in the center.
Cut in squares.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cheese bread
directions: In small saucepan, heat milk just until bubbles form around edges of pan; remove from heat.
Add sugar and salt, stirring until dissolved; let cool to lukewarm.
If possible, check temperature of warm water with thermometer.
Sprinkle yeast over water in large bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in milk mixture, onion, cheese, dill weed and 2 cups flour. Beat with portable electric mixer until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Gradually add remaining flour; mix in last of it with hand until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface. Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.

title: saucy hot dogs
directions: Mix jelly and barbecue sauce until well blended.
Cut hot dogs into bite-sized pieces.
Put hog dogs in crock-pot.
Cover with sauce.
Heat on high until sauce is hot.
Turn to low, heat 1/2 hour.
Can leave in crock-pot to serve.
Keep turned on to low.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; add eggs and blend well.
Add milk and cook slowly until slightly thickened.
Allow to cool. Add whipping cream (unwhipped), vanilla and peaches sweetened with 1 cup sugar.
Pour into freezer only 2/3 full and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: mustard sauce for scallops
directions: Arrange scallops on steaming rack; place over boiling water. Cover and steam 10 minutes.
Transfer scallops to lightly buttered individual baking dishes.
saute mushrooms and onion in margarine until onion is tender; set aside.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard; pour over scallops.
Top with mushrooms and onion.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Broil 5 inches from heat 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until strings a hair.
Add peanuts and cook until gold.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Add soda and pour on large greased cookie sheet.

title: molded cream cheese mints
directions: Soften cream cheese in large mixer bowl.
Add powdered sugar gradually until mixture becomes stiff.
Add flavoring.
(For more than 1 color, separate mixture into individual bowls at this point.)
Add coloring, a little at a time, to reach desired color. Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Press ball into mold.
Unmold at once.
Makes 90 candies.

title: maggie's frijole dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mash pinto beans with a potato masher until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill for several hours before serving. Yields 2 cups.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: railroad corn bread
directions: Brown beef and onion in pan; drain.
Add other ingredients. Put into casserole dish.

title: texas blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water. Add blueberries, pecans and pineapple. Let mixture set. Mix cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Spread over jello and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans. Let set overnight.

title: green chili and rice casserole
directions: Mix together rice, soup, sour cream and green chilies. Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.

title: potato balls
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Place cooled mashed potatoes in a covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Place potatoes in a large bowl.
Add eggs, flour, bread crumbs, and salt.
Mix well.
Roll mixture into balls about 1 1/2 in diameter.
Using a large sauce pan bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Place balls in boiling water.
When balls rise to top, about 3 minutes, remove from water. Serve hot.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine shredded slaw, carrots and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour, then press off juice.
Boil together vinegar, water, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed for 1 minute.
Cool and pour over cabbage mixture.
Put in boxes and freeze.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup oleo and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix soda in milk; add to above.
Mix in 2 cups flour, salt, apples, nutmeats and vanilla.
Mix 2 tablespoons oleo, 2 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Sprinkle on top and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hamburger-tator tot casserole
directions: Put raw ground beef in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chop onion and press into ground beef.
Layer cheese on top of meat.
Pour soup over cheese.
Put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° until Tater Tots are brown.

title: crock-pot spaghetti
directions: Brown ground meat well in skillet and place in crock-pot.
Add all remaining ingredients except dry spaghetti.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 to 5 hours.
Turn to high last hour and stir in dry spaghetti.

title: chicken broccoli oriental
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook chicken, 1/2 at a time, until browned.
Add onion and peppers. Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes; cook time:
20 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli salad(prepare ahead)
directions: Wash broccoli and trim off leaves.
Remove stalks and cut florets into bite size pieces.
Do the same with cauliflower. Combine all veggies in large bowl and squeeze the juice of 1 lemon over all.
Gently toss, adding oil and vinegar.
Add seasoned salt and pepper.
The dressing should be light so the veggies will not "swim" in liquid.
Marinate at least 2 hours.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break crackers coarsely into pastry-lined pan.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in pan; boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Flute edges.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Cook shells according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water.

title: a garden for life
directions: In the first row of peas plant prayer, promptness, politeness, preparedness and perseverance.

title: taco bean dip
directions: Chop real, real fine because this is served with Tostitos.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Sift flour, salt, and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture, alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes and then invert.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks one at a time. Alternate flour and sour cream.
Add soda, extracts and mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla together well.
Pour into pie crust and add enough milk to fill pie crust.
Sprinkle mixture with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then 300° until done.
(Done if table knife inserted comes out clean.)

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Process oil, vinegar, 2 Tbsp. basil, green onion, parmesan cheese, salt & pepper in blender or food processor until smooth. Put pasta, bell pepper strips, tomato wedges, nuts, and olives in a large bowl. Pour in dressing: toss to mix.
Roll cheese cubes in remaining basil to coat and add to salad. Sprinkle with oregano. Toss lightly. Serve at room temperature.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together; roll in small balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 12 1/2 to 15 minutes at 300°.
Be sure not to overcook.

title: chess pie
directions: Toss sugar, flour and corn meal in bowl with fork.
Add eggs, milk, butter and lemon juice; stir until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine nuts, dates, candies, coconut and melted butter.
Mix well.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, soda and milk.
Pour over nut mixture.
Mix well.
Cook in large round cake pan at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Chop green pepper, onion and jalapenos; set aside.
Put eggs and oil in bowl; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk.
Add Mexican corn; fold in chopped vegetables and Cheddar cheese.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° until firm in center (25 to 30 minutes).

title: orange juice pork chops
directions: Rinse pork chops and lightly sprinkle both sides with Season-All.
Spray large skillet with cooking spray.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
Add orange juice, water, salt and parsley. Bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes over medium-low heat until liquid is absorbed by rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: noodles
directions: Mix together.
Roll out on floured board and cut into strips. Cut in 1/8-inch thick.
Boil in salted water until tender.

title: no fail pie crust(alma macfarline)
directions: Put egg and vinegar in one cup and fill with cold water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut lard into flour until coarse grained.
Add water and egg mix.
Divide and roll or freeze 1/2.
Can be rolled over and over and come out tender.
Great for a non-baker.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese and sour cream.
Drain all fruit and add to mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: filling balls
directions: Mix
well
and
make into balls size of your choice and put on
cookie
sheet that has been covered with foil.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered or till brown at 350°.

title: heaven on a bone
directions: Arrange chicken breast in a broiler pan lined with foil. Brush butter and honey over chicken. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Mix bread crumbs with more butter. Remove chicken from oven and place crumbs on top of each chicken piece. Return to oven for 20 minutes. Sprinkle grated cheeses over chicken (this will form a sort of skin over chicken). Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: good morning pumpkin pancakes
directions: In large bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour onto lightly greased griddle.
Cook until top surface is bubbly and edges are dry.
Turn and cook until golden.
Serve with syrup or honey.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all and place in skillet.
Let come to a hard boil.
Cook 7 minutes or until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 stick butter and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Add pecans.
Stir until it begins to thicken.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: monterey bake
directions: Combine rice, sour cream, milk, salt, green chilies and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon into a buttered, shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry-glazed cheesecake
directions: In a bowl, stir together graham cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar. Mix in melted butter and press into a 9-inch spring-form pan to make crust. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool. Reduce oven to 300°.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg; coat with cornstarch.
Deep fry in oil until golden brown.

title: pineapple macadamia nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Using a fork, mix together nuts, drained pineapple tidbits, soda and salt. Add shortening and hot crushed pineapple.
Mix all together well. Beat eggs; beat in vanilla and sugar.
Stir in flour.
Add pineapple mixture and stir just until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Bread may be served warm or cold.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: raisin apple pie
directions: Cook raisins, flour, sugar and vinegar and water until thick. Add apples, cinnamon and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cover with top crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: molasses masies(patty pans)
directions: Put all ingredients in large iron skillet.
Boil slowly until 310° on candy thermometer or until a little dropped in cold water makes a hard thread.
Butter tiny muffin tins.
Fill 1/3 full and cool in refrigerator.
Nuts may be added before pouring in tins. Just put nuts in tins before pouring.

title: chinese chop suey
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat until crumbly; drain.
Add rest of the ingredients through soy sauce.
Stir in the 1/2 cup of uncooked rice.
Put in casserole, cover and bake 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more, then sprinkle chow mein noodles on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: curried corn soup
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add curry powder and stir until smooth. Add onion then corn, stirring slowly.
Then add cream.
Heat through.

title: bread pretzels
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Mix in flour and sugar.
Roll in pretzel shapes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white, sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place the peaches in a shallow 2-quart baking dish and sprinkle the cake mix on top of them.
Now sprinkle sugar over the cake mix.
Melt the butter and drizzle over the top.
Sprinkle nuts over the whole thing and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Mash down the dry mix and bake again for 20 minutes more.

title: wild rice
directions: Combine the wild rice, vegetables and chicken stock in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook on high for 10 minutes.
Continue cooking on low for 40 minutes.
Let rice rest in the oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: swiss steak
directions: Do not pound meat.
Brown steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Put in a roasting pan (it splatters).
Add tomato sauce, onion and celery and enough water to cover meat.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. If gravy is not thick, thicken.
This may be adjusted to personal tastes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine vegetables with salt.
Let stand 10 minutes and drain.
Add celery seed, allspice, turmeric, sugar and vinegar. Heat to boiling.
Can in sterilized jars.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: grilled lamb chops
directions: Pour enough olive oil in dish (big enough to hold chops) to cover bottom.
Sprinkle rosemary, thyme and garlic evenly over oil. Place chops in dish and marinate overnight (or several hours), turning once.
Chop are best grilled, but can be broiled.
The are best if served slightly rare.

title: semolina gnocchi
directions: Heat milk over medium-low heat in large saucepan to 180° or until tiny bubbles form around edge (do not boil).
Remove from heat; gradually add flour, salt and nutmeg, stirring until well blended.
Place pan over low heat; cook 1 minute, stirring vigorously, until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball. Add egg, stirring vigorously.
Cook 1 minute (mixture will be thick).
Remove from heat and add cheese, stirring vigorously, until well blended.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Spoon meat into 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over casserole. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cut dry ingredients with Crisco. Add other ingredients.
Roll, cut and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen biscuits.

title: granola bars
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Add syrup, salt, vanilla, sugar and oatmeal.
Mix well.
With damp spatula, press mixture into well greased 15 1/2 by 10 1/2-inch (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
During the last 2 minutes of baking time, sprinkle on the chocolate chips.
When they soften take pan from oven and spread chips evenly on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into squares while warm.
Recut when cool.

title: scandinavian almond bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and almond extract and beat well. Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide dough into fourths.
Form each into a 12-inch roll.
Place 2 rolls 4 to 5-inches apart on an ungreased
cookie sheet.
Flatten until 3-inches wide.
Repeat with remaining rolls.
Brush flattened rolls with milk and sprinkle with almonds.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and boil eggplant until tender; mash.
Cook sausage and onion until done.
Crumble.
Mix all together and bake at 350° until set like dressing.

title: quick and easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in 375° oven.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Pour in the melted margarine.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla, mixing well.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding dry pudding mix last.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: fat free salad with fiber
directions: Tear up lettuce into bite size pieces.
Add beans, onions and tomatoes into bowl.
Add vinegar.

title: banana n oats
directions: Mash bananas and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade irish cream
directions: Beat eggs well. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into bottle and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator at least 2 weeks.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: In a small saucepan, place 1 cup of brown sugar and shortening.
Melt together.
Place in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Peel apples and slice. Add cinnamon.
Pour over brown sugar mixture.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients; pour over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: holiday fruit ball
directions: Heat marshmallows, milk and margarine over low heat until melted.
Mix crumbs, fruit and nuts; pour mixture over them. Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.
Store.

title: heath bar torte
directions: Combine graham crackers, nuts and melted butter. Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat 5 egg whites with the cream of tartar.
Add the sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of crust and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: crispy lunch pickles(bread and butter type)
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Chop onions and peppers and combine with cucumbers.
Add salt and let stand 3 hours, stirring occasionally; drain.

title: chinese rice
directions: Chop celery, green onions and green pepper.
Saute with bacon until bacon is cooked and vegetables are tender.
Add soy sauce to cover the bottom of pan.
Add cooked rice to vegetable mixture.

title: southwestern tuna bake
directions: In large pot of boiling water, cook bow tie pasta following package directions. Drain.

title: carl's mom's pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake on hot grill.

title: no bake rice crispie cookies(quick and easy)
directions: Combine the white sugar, dark syrup and bring to a boil.
Mix in the vanilla and peanut butter until well blended.
Add Rice Crispies.
Drop on wax paper.

title: chocolate-coated coconut balls(bonbons)
directions: Melt butter slow and add milk.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add coconut and pecans.
Chill.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat and dip each candy ball in chocolate with a toothpick.
Remove candy from chocolate quickly and place on wax paper.
Use another toothpick to push ball from inserted toothpick.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine
sugars,
oleo and milk. Bring to rolling boil, stirring
constantly.
Boil
5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly (scorches easily).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate
pieces
until
melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat
until
well blended.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: best baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into large pan. Place strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great for cookouts and big family outings.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger meat, onions, green peppers and garlic clove. Mix all the ingredients in heavy pot.
Salt to taste.
Cook slowly on medium heat about 4 to 5 hours.

title: cornbread batter
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Add cornmeal and mix well. Add buttermilk and egg.
Then add salad oil.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and nuts until golden brown over medium heat, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda until mixture foams.
Pour onto aluminum foil.
Let cool; break and eat.

title: ham spread
directions: Combine all ingedients, mixing well.
Serve on crackers, toast squares or rounds.

title: pepper onion relish
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cook until slightly thickened (about 45 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Pack the boiling hot relish into clean, hot jars, filling to top of jars. Seal tightly.
Store in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 stick margarine.
Boil squash; drain and mash.
Combine squash with soup and onion.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine and mix with 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
Put into casserole dish a layer of squash, cheese and layer of cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: baked hash brown casserole
directions: Mix onion, soup, 1/2 of the butter, sour cream, cheese and potatoes.
Mix rest of oleo with corn flakes; spread on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar in a mixing bowl. Add pineapple and pour entire mixture in

the graham cracker pie crust. Layer sliced bananas over the mixture and top with Cool Whip. Swirl chocolate syrup over the Cool Whip and top with chopped pecans, if desired. Chill for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender. Drain. Rinse with cold water. Add all other ingredients. Mix with mayonnaise.

title: french cream frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick.
Cool.
Cream 1 cup sugar, Crisco and vanilla.
Mix all together and beat until very creamy. Spread on cooled cake.

title: thanksgiving jellied salad
directions: Drain pineapple; keep juice.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cold water, pineapple juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir sugar into ground fruits; fold into jello.
Add pineapple, oranges, celery and walnuts.
Pour into ring mold. Chill until firm.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: quick bake beans
directions: Mix together on stove top; add all ingredients until simmer. Remove.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: sherried "sea leg" soup
directions: Combine soups in saucepan; mix well.
Stir in sherry, milk and mushrooms.
Add sea legs; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: raisin bars(diabetic dessert)
directions: In a saucepan combine raisins and apple juice.
Bring to boil and then cool.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, egg and vegetable oil.
Add raisin mixture and blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture into lightly oiled 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle on grated orange rind.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 2-inch bars.
These are delightful served plain but on special occasions can be topped as desired.
Yield:
14 bars.

title: butterscotch banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In a large bowl, combine bananas, sugar, egg and butter. Beat until creamy. Gradually add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Mix until well blended. Stir in 1 cup nuts and butterscotch bits. Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle remaining 1/3 cup nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar. Make well in dry ingredients. Add eggs and oil, stirring only until moist. Stir in berries, pecans and food coloring. Spoon batter into 2 greased 8-inch loaf pans and bake for 1 hour or until bread tests done with a toothpick. Let stand overnight before cutting.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease dish.
Empty fruit into dish.
Dump cake mix over top of fruit.
Place pats of butter over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
After butter melts and cake starts to bake, if any cake mix is still powder, use a little more butter in those places.

title: waldorf slaw salad
directions: Combine cabbage, apple and raisins.
Pour dressing over this and chill to let flavors blend.
Before serving, garnish with apple slices dipped in lemon juice to prevent browning and walnuts.

title: seafood salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure into bowl the sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well with wooden spoon, then add raisins.
Measure and sift together 2 times the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add this to the shortening mixture and mix well.
Then stir in oats.

title: chocolate berry trifle
directions: Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. Gently stir in 1 cup whipped topping. Place 1/2 the brownie cubes in 2-quart serving bowl. Top with 1/2 each of the pudding mixture, strawberries and remaining whipped topping. Repeat layers. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter and 1/2 cup sugar. Place on bottom and sides of a spring-form pan, reserving a few crumbs for garnish on top of finished cake.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in top of double boiler.
Mix in noodles to a good consistency.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: cinnamon sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy. Blend in sour cream, flour, soda and baking powder.
Add vanilla.

title: grated raw sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until lemon color.
Add milk, melted butter, vanilla, salt and grated sweet potatoes.
Bake in buttered baking dish in a 375° oven for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Stir in brown sugar, mustard and salt. Add cooked carrots.
Heat, stirring constantly, until carrots are glazed, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: uncle jim's devil's food cake
directions: Beat the sugar, margarine and eggs until fluffy and then add the cocoa, buttermilk, soda and flour.
Mix until creamy, then add the hot water (blend in) and walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Top with your favorite cream cheese frosting.
Cover and place in the refrigerator as flavor improves and the cake is more moist.

title: egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover the bottom with chopped ham, then layer bread cubes on top of the ham.
Finally layer cheese cubes over the top.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over the top.
Cover and refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325° or until center is set.
Serves 8 to 16 people.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Stir in grated chocolate and chocolate chips.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.
Top cake with powdered sugar and grated chocolate.

title: creamy cole slaw(like served at cock of the walk)
directions: Slice or chop one head of cabbage as fine as possible.
Mix equal amounts of vinegar and sugar; pour enough over cabbage to saturate well.
Let stand for several hours, preferably overnight, in the refrigerator.
Add mayonnaise and milk or buttermilk. Season with mustard, salt, pepper and poppy seed to taste.
Bell pepper, chopped very fine, is a nice addition.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Grease tube pan.
Beat egg, sugar and margarine together. Stir in dry ingredients.
Stir in applesauce. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in greased tube pan.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour applesauce in casserole dish. Mix together flour, sugar and margarine. Mixture will be crumbly. Pour over applesauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Thaw out pie shells completely.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 1 pie shell.
Take other pie shell, put on wax paper or foil and roll out flat using a glass or rolling pin.
Fit on top of pie and crimp edges together.
Cut about 5 or 6 slits in center (to vent) and dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is light brown.
Place on pizza pan to bake in case of spills.

title: jiffy scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sour cream, butter and corn.
Fold in Jiffy mix and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and cream of tartar together.
Add to cake with flavorings.
Fold in coconut with a spoon.
Cook in cold oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bit of sunshine casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Cube Velveeta cheese.
Put on top of vegetables.
Crumble Ritz crackers.
Place on top.
Slice butter.
Place on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni lasagna
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink and drain. Add water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, bouillon and seasonings. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes. In a bowl, combine eggs, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Spread 1/2 cup meat sauce into a greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Layer with four noodles, the cottage cheese mixture and pepperoni.
Top with remaining noodles and meat sauce.
Sprinkle with mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until heated through.

title: broiled catfish filets
directions: Rinse and dry filets.
Season and set aside.
Saute green onion and parsley in butter.
Add chopped shrimp and cook until pink. Add crabmeat and bread crumbs.
Moisten with 4 tablespoons chicken broth.
Place filets in foil lined pan and broil 3 minutes, then turn and baste with lemon juice and butter.
Place seafood dressing on filets and broil for approximately 5 minutes. Serve with lemon juice and butter.

title: california casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef with green pepper and onion until the meat is browned and the vegetables are tender; drain.
Add next 11 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add noodles; mix well.
Pour into a Dutch oven or large baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, return to oven and bake for 10 minutes or until the cheese melts.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oats, flour, powder, soda and salt.
In second bowl mix peanut butter and margarine; add sugars.
Beat in egg, banana and vanilla.
Stir in flour; mix and drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 4 minutes before removing.

title: chicken minestrone
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, chicken, zucchini squash and tomatoes.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until tender.
Yield: 9 cups (136 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or two 9-inch or three 8-inch round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake oblong 45 to 50 minutes, layers 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: unbaked chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine/butter, sugar and chocolate in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add one egg and beat for 5 minutes. Add second egg and beat 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell. Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: pastel party popcorn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, stir in marshmallows, allow them to soften.
Blend in gelatin until mixture is evenly covered. Drizzle marshmallow mixture over popcorn and mix thoroughly; cool. Store in tightly covered container and set in a cool place.

title: apple-peanut salad
directions: Put apples, celery and peanuts in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over mixture.
Stir to coat.
Serve on salad greens, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken tortilla roll-ups
directions: You just cook it.
When it is cold then you eat it in the kitchen with ice cream sandwiches and sprinkles.

title: lasagna(original)
directions: Cook ground chuck, spices and tomato sauce and puree until thick, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.
While this is cooking, cook 1 package lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Then mix well beaten eggs, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese with 2 tablespoons parsley flakes.
Layer in a 9 x 15-inch pan, starting with noodles, then cheese sauce, then meat sauce and then shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Add one more layer of each and top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon pepper mushrooms
directions: Mix all together except mushroom caps; stuff the 8 large mushrooms with mixture.
Preheat oven to 450° and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ranch style veggie dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth; refrigerate for 1 hour and serve with crackers and bite-size fresh vegetables such as carrots, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: In a large bowl combine frozen vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup of the cheese, sour cream and pepper. Stir in half the french onions. Spoon into a two quart baking dish. Bake covered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer or until mixture is heated through. Makes 6 servings.

title: swiss n' chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except walnuts. Spoon in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam spray.
Mix peanuts, sugar and water in a saucepan.
Heat on medium, stirring occasionally.
In about 10 minutes the mixture will crystallize and begin to coat the peanuts.
Now spread the mixture on cookie sheet and bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring the mixture occasionally. Store in tightly covered container.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Great for chipped ham sandwiches.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Add all ingredients and blend with a mixer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Pack firmly into a stone baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: me-maw blackwell's sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar, salt, soda and margarine together.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add eggs (one at a time) and flour, alternating. Add flavoring.
Slowly mix all together.
Grease a tube pan with a nonstick cooking spray and blot excess with paper towel.
Pour mixture into tube pan and bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
(Temperature depends on oven.)

title: white pancetta sauce
directions: Cut bacon into small piece and fry well with garlic and pepper.
Partially drain.
Spread over cooked capellini and sprinkle
with cheese.
Stir gently and serve.

title: fried turkey
directions: You will need a large stock pot (36 to 40 quart).

title: mrs. whitten's creamed rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Beat yolks, milk, sugar, flour and salt together and pour over rhubarb.
Place cubes of oleo over top.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cover with meringue made by beating egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar and pinch of baking powder.
Cover pie completely to edges and brown in oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a baking dish, sprinkle 1 1/2 c. crushed Ritz's crackers on top.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, brown sugar and pretzels in bowl.
Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
In medium bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries; mix well.
Chill until partially set. Mix cream cheese and sugar in bowl.
Fold in whipped topping. Spread over baked crust.
Spread gelatin over cream cheese mixture.
Chill overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Melt margarine and combine with flour, 3/4 cup sugar and other ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold into first mixture; pour into buttered casserole dish, place in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before serving.

title: original dill dip
directions: Mix all together; store in covered container overnight to allow blending.
Serve with various cut up vegetables.
Can also be used as a salad dressing.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Spoon pineapple over top. Sprinkle cheese over pineapple.
Combine margarine and cracker crumbs.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tailgate cheese spread
directions: Shred the cheese and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Cream the butter lightly and blend with the shredded cheese.
Mix in the paprika and 1/4 cup of the whiskey until well blended.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Slowly add the remaining whiskey until well blended.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: ann's turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 cup canned milk and melted butter or margarine together.
Pour slightly less than 1/2 batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until firm, at 350°.
Melt the caramels with 2/3 cup canned milk; pour mixture on top of cake mix.
Top with nuts.
Add a layer of all chocolate chips.
Cover with the remainder of batter.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Do not overbake!
Enjoy!

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk; mix well.
Pour mixture into margarine; do not stir.
Pour 3 1/2 cup fruit and juice over the batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until cake part is done.

title: christmas apple jelly
directions: Combine apple juice, food coloring and pectin in large saucepan.
Bring mixture to full boil.
Stir in sugar until it dissolves.
Bring to boil again.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; skim if necessary.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal. Yields 7 half pints.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook until onion is tender.

title: luscious lemon angel food cake
directions: Cut cake into 4 layers.
In medium bowl mix together lemon filling and yogurt.
Spread filling between each layer, but not on top of cake.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in butter.
Combine all ingredients except shrimp and cook several hours.
Add flour or cornstarch to thicken.
Add shrimp last couple of minutes of cooking.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in a skillet and pour off all fat. Add pepper, onions and garlic.
Cook until tender. Put meat mix in large cooking pot and add other ingredients. Cook on very low heat for 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
The secret is in the long, slow cooking.

title: bacon cream cheese ribbon sandwiches
directions: Cream cheese, bacon (crumbled) and chopped olives together. Add enough mayonnaise to make mixture spread easily.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Spread onto bread.
Cut into ribbon sandwiches.

title: mama's angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix next 5 ingredients well.
Add Crisco, yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix well, then place in refrigerator or shape into desired shape.
Let double in size and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken #2
directions: Combine crumbs, Parmesan (1/4 cup), oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange skin side down.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 minutes more. Meanwhile, blend soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and remaining Parmesan.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Fold in Crisco.
Add water and mix together.
Knead.
Makes 1 two crust pie.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine shortening, butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Gradually add flour, baking soda and salt into creamed mixture.
Add chips.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts).
Roll in chopped nuts. Chill.

title: low-fat gravy
directions: Pour pan drippings into glass measuring cup.
Let broth stand until fat rises to the top.
Skim off fat.
For gravy, make paste of 1 tablespoon each broth and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat. Whisk in 1 cup broth and stir until gravy thickens.
Makes 1 cup. Each serving (1 tablespoon) is 5 calories.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Spread crackers with peanut butter to make a sandwich, set aside.
Melt the bark in a double boiler, when melted, dip the sandwich in the bark, then place on wax paper to set up.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended (mixture is too stiff to thoroughly blend in all of dry ingredients).
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Microwave at High 2 minutes; remove, stir fast until smooth.
Blend in nuts.
Can add chunky peanut butter, about 3/4 cup.
Pour in pan 8 x 4 x 3-inch.
Chill 1 hour; cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil, debone and chop chicken into small pieces.
Combine soup and sour cream; fold in chicken.
Place in a greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle poppy seed evenly over chicken mixture. Crumble crackers evenly over casserole; drizzle butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: stone soup
directions: Put in the amounts of spices and vegetables that you want. Let it boil undisturbed.
Let it bubble.
Let it brew.
Share Stone Soup with everyone.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Wash chicken thighs and pat dry.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and let stand 5 minutes.
Dip chicken in beaten eggs.
Fry until nearly done.
Spray large pan with nonstick spray.
Mix sugar, juice, catsup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Put chicken in pan and pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 300° oven or until sauce is thick.
Put chicken on platter and spoon remaining sauce over top.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
Cream oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix milk and pudding mix together and combine with cheese mixture.
Mix well and fold in whipped topping.
Layer ingredients in flower pot or sand bucket, starting with cookie crumbs, then pudding mixture and ending with cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate.
Keeps for days.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in soup until tender.
Mix all ingredients except chops, salt and pepper.
Put in baking dish. Place chops on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes; uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fried bananas
directions: Amount of each ingredient will depend on how many you want to fix.
Cut bananas into 1-inch slices.
Dip in egg or milk, then in coating of your choice.
Cook in 1-inch of oil heated to 375° until light brown.
Serve hot.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and Eagle Brand milk.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crumb crust.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in two layers. When cool, split layers to make four layers.

title: egg swans
directions: For the filling, combine chopped shrimp, dill and garlic powder.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten the mixture.
Slice hard-boiled eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks and store for another use.
Generously fill the egg whites with the shrimp mixture.

title: spinach bisque soup
directions: Boil spinach and chicken broth until spinach separates.
Saute onion and margarine, then add 4 tablespoons cornstarch to make a roux (pasty).
Add this to soup mix and whisk until smooth.
Add Cheez Whiz, grated Cheddar and Parmesan cheese.
Stir well.
Add half and half.
Serve with hard roll and slice of ham.
Bon appetit!

title: spaghetti alla carbonara(spaghetti with bacon and egg sauce)
directions: Melt butter with oil in a small saucepan.
When butter foams, add pancetta.
Saute over medium heat until lightly colored.
Keep warm.
Beat egg yolks in a large shallow serving dish.
Beat in cream, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
This dish should be quite peppery.
Fill a very large saucepan 2/3 full with salted water.
Bring water to a boil.
Add spaghetti.
Bring water back to a boil and cook spaghetti, uncovered, until tender but firm to the bite (al dente) 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain spaghetti and place in dish with egg yolk mixture.
Toss quickly.
Add sauteed pancetta and toss gently until mixed.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together margarine, peanut butter, graham crackers and powdered sugar.
Pat out evenly in a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt chips and shortening.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Let stand until chocolate has hardened.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large, oblong pan.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers (sliced) in brine made of salt and water for 48 hours.
Drain.
Cover with boiling water for 24 hours.
Drain and cover with boiling water to which 1 tablespoon alum has been added.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Make syrup of 6 cups sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boil; add cinnamon and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and heat syrup and add 1 cup sugar.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Heat syrup and add 1 cup sugar and cucumbers. Boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars; cover with syrup and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: tropical banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Combine Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamed.
Add eggs, bananas and sour cream. Beat until well blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Add at low speed of electric mixer.
Mix until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cooling racks.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Cook the margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup for 5 minutes. Stir in the salt, vanilla and soda.
Stir over popcorn; put in a large pan.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: yummy cupcakes
directions: Mix and refrigerate until cake batter is ready.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add liquid slowly.
Chill overnight.
Add bacon bits before serving.

title: italian beef
directions: Place meat in roasting pan.
Combine all other ingredients. Heat and pour over meat.
Cover, bake at 350° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Turn often to baste.
Cool.
Remove from meat juice, slice meat very thin.
Add cornstarch to meat juice to make thin gravy.
Return meat to gravy, keep warm.
Serve on split hard rolls.

title: tummy yummies
directions: In bowl, combine sugar and crackers.
In saucepan, melt oleo, peanut butter and add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Press lightly into jelly roll pan.
Cool in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Cover with melted chocolate chips.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions thinly.
Saute in butter and oil until clear. Stir in salt and sugar.
Cook until golden brown (about 30 minutes), stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour.
Add beef bouillon, water and wine.
Bring to a boil while stirring; simmer for 30 minutes.
Salt to taste; ladle into ovenproof bowls. Top with French bread, sprinkled with Swiss cheese.
Place under broiler for a few minutes to melt cheese.

title: bacon lettuce and tomato pie
directions: Mix onion and flour; sprinkle in pie shell.
Top with tomato, bacon and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°, uncovered.
Top with lettuce and serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in moderate oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: egg-bean sandwiches
directions: Heat beans until hot; spread muffin halves with beans. Sprinkle cheese over beans; arrange tomatoes on cheese.
Heat water (1 1/2 to 2-inches) to boiling; reduce to simmer.
Break each egg into measuring cup or saucer, holding cup close to water's surface.
Slip 1 egg at a time into water.
Cook until desired doneness, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove eggs from water with slotted spoon.
Place egg on tomatoes; sprinkle with onions. Makes 6 servings.

title: pie crusts for 2 pies
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Combine water and vinegar.
Cut in shortening then slowly add water and vinegar solution.
Add egg. Mix well then form into 4 balls.
Use rolling pin to spread out.

title: white trash
directions: Combine Rice Chex, peanuts and raisins.
Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Chex mix.
Coat well.
Set aside to cool for 3 to 4 hours.
When completely cool, toss powdered sugar over entire mixture.
Store in airtight containers.

title: sour cream corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or in a muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins or serves 6 to 8 when baked in a square pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: steamed dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; combine egg, milk and fat.
Add to dry ingredients to make soft dough.
Drop from teaspoon into broth or stew.
(Should be 3 cups broth; add water if necessary.)
Steam 15 minutes.

title: broccoli rice bake
directions: In skillet, saute diced onion in melted oleo.
Stir in Cheez Whiz.
Stir until smooth.
In a large mixing bowl, mix rice, soups, water and mushrooms.
Add thawed broccoli.
Stir in melted cheese mixture.
Bake in casserole dish for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions; drain well and chill.
Combine with cooked and cubed chicken and remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves, optional.
Makes 8 servings.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add flour and milk.
Add flavorings.
Grease tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: hummus dip
directions: Grind cooked chickpeas in blender and add all other ingredients except parsley.
Stir parsley in by hand.
Refrigerate, but serve at room temperature if possible.
Flavor increases over time. Really good for 1-2 days, strong after that.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread; crumble in casserole dish.
Cook pinto beans; pour over corn bread.
Chop tomatoes, pepper and onion; layer over pintos.
Add bacon bits.
Mix mayo and pickle juice; pour over mixture.
Add sliced dill pickles on top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving enough Tater Tots to top casserole dish.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots and then with your favorite cheese and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare the rice with the water. Set aside. Cut up the bacon and fry. Add the onion and Spam. Brown, then add the soy sauce. Add rice and heat.

title: peggy's rice
directions: Brown rice in skillet with margarine.
Pour into casserole and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump ingredients (in layers) in a 8 x 12-inch ungreased baking pan in this order:
pie filling, pineapple, cake mix, butter, coconut and pecans.
Do not mix, just dump in.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix in order given and bake.

title: california raisin cake
directions: Grind peel and raisins.
Cream butter and 1 1/4 cups sugar. Add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix flour and baking soda, add to butter mixture, add raisin mixture, mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done. Combine 1/4 cup remaining sugar, mandarin juice and Curacao, spoon over cake immediately upon removing from oven.

title: summer fruit salad(healthful eating)
directions: Layer the lettuce on a chilled dinner plate.
Spoon yogurt into individual custard cups; place on center or side of plate. Surround with fresh fruits.

title: raspberry jell
directions: Combine tomatoes and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 15 minutes. Pour over jello and stir.
Pour into jars and refrigerate.

title: turnip greens
directions: Put all ingredients into iron skillet.
Cook over medium heat. Heat, uncovered, until most of liquid evaporates.
Serve hot.

title: punch
directions: Mix water and sugar well.
Add vanilla, almond extract, red food coloring and lemon juice.
Mix.
Add pineapple juice.
Add ice cubes at least one hour before serving, so they can melt in.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sweet potatoes and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Mix well and add salt, eggs, cinnamon, milk, vanilla and 1 stick melted oleo.
Blend all ingredients well.
Spray 9 x 13-inch oblong dish with Pam and pour above mixture into the dish. In a medium size bowl, add brown sugar and flour.
Add 2/3 cup melted oleo and pecans.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Spoon over potato mixture and bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
You can also top with mini marshmallows and bake a few extra minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes, onion, celery and bouillon in pot; add water 1 inch above mixture.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cook until potatoes are done.
Don't overcook.
Drain half of liquid.
Place back on medium heat and add margarine and melt.
Slowly pour in milk.
Heat until hot; do not overheat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: amanda's rice and ham
directions: Put ham on top of rice and top with cheese.
Microwave long enough to melt cheese then season to taste with soy sauce.

title: spiced apple spread
directions: Blend or mix together all ingredients until smooth.
Makes 16 servings, 1 tablespoon each.
Great on muffins, rolls or toast!

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil peppers until soft.
Take stems off.
Put peppers in blender.
Drain juice off tomatoes into blender.
Put all spices into blender.
Turn blender on until peppers are dissolved.
Add tomatoes; turn on just long enough to make tomatoes chunky.

title: cinnamon kites
directions: Separate rolls into sections.
Mix egg and milk.
Dip each section of roll into egg mixture.
Fry in deep fat (as for frying doughnuts).
Watch closely, turning over.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Toss each kite in cinnamon and sugar.
Serve hot. Makes 12 servings.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup gravy.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Pour remaining gravy over loaf and bake for another 1/2 hour or until done in middle.

title: apple buntings
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Coat apple slices with butter; roll in cinnamon sugar.
Roll each biscuit out very thin. Place apple slices in center.
Bring all sides up to top and pinch together so totally enclosing apple inside.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: Season meat; saute and drain.
Combine meal, salt, onion, cheese and peppers in large bowl.
Stir in egg and milk.
Add corn.
Put half in baking dish.
Put meat next.
Add rest of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: donna's mexican dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mash into pie dish.
Next, in the order listed, layer the remaining ingredients into dish.
Put in a 350° oven and bake until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Cream butter with vanilla together.
Add sugar (both brown and white) and salt, mixing well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add syrup; beat well.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until pie has set.

title: vidalia sweet onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Press into 8-inch pie plate.
Saute until clear (but not brown) the onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Spoon into crust.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper; pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika over onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test with knife; when it comes out clean, it's ready.
Garnish with parsley.

title: onion, ham and cheese chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in water about 10 minutes until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Cook onion in margarine until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour and pepper. Add milk and potato water all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add ham and cheese.
Stir to melt cheese. Don't boil.
Serves 8.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add onion, celery and carrots; cook 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and dill.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: busy day cake
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into a mixing bowl.
Add soft shortening, milk, unbeaten eggs and vanilla, all at once.
Beat all for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, milk and bananas; mix well. Sift flour, soda and salt. Add these and chopped nuts to first mixture. Bake for 1 hour in well-greased loaf pan at 325°. Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: orange slice cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, butter and milk.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, orange slices, pecans and coconut. Combine both mixtures and pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: easy fried apple pies
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Cook over medium-high heat.
Add sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Roll out 1 biscuit 1/8-inch thick.
Spread 1 tablespoon margarine on top of biscuit.
Put 1 tablespoon apples in middle biscuit.
Fold over in 1/2.
Seal with prongs of fork. Fry in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and chili powder to taste.
Drain off excess fat.
(Can be put in colander and run hot water over.)
Add soup, catsup and mustard.
Simmer.

title: rotel dip
directions: Cut cheese up into small pieces and melt in microwave.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and place back in microwave until cheese is completely melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vegie bites
directions: Press rolls in lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Cream the cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix.
Spread over cool crust.
Chop red pepper, green pepper, broccoli and mushrooms.
Put this on top of the cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Use more if you wish. Refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw dough as directed on package and let rise in warm place. Separate dough into halves. Grease hands and cookie sheet thoroughly. Spread dough out into a long rectangle. Brush inside of dough with egg and place pepperoni in a row down the middle of each loaf. Top with mozzarella cheese and fold one side over the mixture, then the other and press to seal. Fold ends and turn seam side down. Brush with beaten egg. Can put both loaves on same baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 - 25 minutes. Cool slightly and slice to serve.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, salt and butter in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until chocolate is melted and ingredients are well blended.
Pour into 2 buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Chill until firm.
Yields 4 pounds.

title: raspberry coconut squares
directions: Put flour,
cup
sugar into mixing bowl and blend. Cut in 1/2
cup
butter
until fine particles.
Add 1 lightly beaten egg and
toss
to
moisten.
With
hands, work mixture until dough forms.
Lightly
flour
hands
and press dough on bottom of
x 9-inch pan which
has been lightly buttered. Spread a thin even coat of jam on the top.
Cream together the 1/4
cup
softened butter
with
remaining
1 cup sugar.
Add remaining 3
eggs, 1 at a time and beating after each addition until
light
and
creamy. Add
coconut and mix well.
Spread over jam.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden. Cool and cut into squares.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice
cucumbers;
add
onions
and peppers.
Add salt. Cover with cracked ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain and combine
remaining
ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture and heat to boiling.
Place in hot jars and process in a hot water bath 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: In a bowl, combine pineapple, cranberry sauce and oranges. Fold in whipped topping and orange peel.
Serve in lettuce leaves if desired; store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and graham crackers.
Cover and cook in microwave for 2-3 minutes.
Press in 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: easy fudge
directions: Bring butter and corn syrup to a boil.
Melt chocolate and add milk; bring to a boil.
Add sugar and salt; stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Beat until thick.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Pour sugar over rhubarb and let stand.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle rhubarb/sugar mixture over cake. Drizzle whipping cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cream and rhubarb sink to bottom to form custard.
Let cool.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over medium heat until sugar melts. Do not stir.
After sugar is melted, cook until it reaches 234°. Remove from heat; add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted, then add marshmallow cream and vanilla, stirring until all is mixed together.
Add nuts.
Butter a jelly roll pan and pour into and let set until it cools.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Place nuts in a large bowl and set aside. In small bowl, beat egg whites, juice, sugar, rind, cinnamon, ginger, allspice and salt.
When well mixed, pour over nuts and toss until thoroughly coated.
In a large shallow pan, spread nuts in a single layer so they do not touch.
Bake, stirring every 15 minutes, until nuts are lightly browned and crispy, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool completely and store in an airtight container. Makes about 5 cups.

title: mexican delight ala east hampton
directions: *For spicier, go to medium and hot.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Put all ingredients together, mixing well. Cook in top of double boiler until thick. Let cool before spreading. Use with any white layer cake or lemon cake.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine
the first 8 ingredients.
Mix together the soups, salad dressing and Amaretto.
Combine with chicken mixture.

title: crispy christmas trees
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan.
Stir in marshmallows.
Cook and stir over low heat til melted.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal & pecans.
Let cool just enough to handle with greased hands.
Shape into trees or cones.
Roll in green sugar.
Looks really festive on a silver tray with powdered sugar dusted on them & the tray.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix pudding and milk with electric mixer until thickened.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip (reserving enough Cool Whip to use as topping).
Mix well.
Layer wafers, bananas and mixture.
Repeat. Top with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Boil strawberry jello, water and crushed pineapple; let cool. After they have cooled, add Cool Whip, cottage cheese, nuts and strawberries.
Mix well and pour into dish.
Let chill well before serving.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash figs, using only firm figs with stems.
Soak for 10 minutes in lime water (1 tablespoon air slaked lime to 1 gallon water).
Drain.
Soak in plain water for 10 minutes.
Drain; let stand in salt water for 10 minutes (1 tablespoon salt to each gallon water).
Drain well, but do not rinse.

title: perfect potluck casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and onion, cook until tender; stir to separate meat.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: lucky apple pie
directions: Mix apple mixture well.
Put in bottom crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 425°. Nice spicy flavor.

title: spuddy snowballs
directions: Cream the cheese; add potatoes, vanilla and salt, blending until smooth.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time, mixing well after each time.
Add 1 cup coconut.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll into balls and then in a bowl of the rest of the coconut.
Cover closely and chill 2 or more hours.
