Much better after mellowing!

title: cherry cream sodas
directions: Scoop ice cream into clear or colored glasses.
Pour syrup over ice cream to taste.
Add 7-Up or Sprite and top with cherry.
Fun to make for parties and bridal or baby showers!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Cook for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: payday cake
directions: Step One:
Mix cake mix, melted butter and egg in mixing bowl. Spread in 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: orange sherbet mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cool slightly.
Add sherbet and oranges, mixing well.
Pour into a mold-sprayed with Pam.
Great with poultry and for dessert.

title: stuffed crown roast of pork flambe
directions: Two rack ribs can be substituted for the crown roast. Tie each rack in a circle.
Place bone tips up on rack in open shallow roasting pan, packing stuffing in center.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening and dry ingredients.
Beat other ingredients and add to dry, blending with a fork until moistened.
Mold dough into 4 or 5 balls.
Chill well (a must!) as dough is very soft. Dough keeps in refrigerator 3 days or may be frozen.

title: microwave candy
directions: In casserole dish, mix all ingredients.
Place in microwave 1 to 2 minutes until chips blend when stirred.
Refrigerate until solid enough to cut into bars.

title: peach conserve
directions: Measure fruit and juice after chopped.
Use 1 1/2 times the amount of sugar.
Put in large heavy pot and cook at 220° until thick, approximately 45 minutes.
While still boiling, add Sure-Jell and put in jars.
Seal.
Makes 18 to 20 small 1/2 pint jars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup with 1/2 cup water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over mixture.
Put stuffing mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake 60 to 75 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix sugar and margarine in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in eggs until blended.
Add bananas and water; beat 30 seconds.
Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts until moistened.
Stir in nuts. Pour into pan.
Bake until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: daddy's chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together; simmer at least 1 hour.

title: mother's broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Melt butter.
Saute celery and onion until clear.
Combine broccoli, vegetables, rice, cheese and mushroom soup; blend well.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak raisins with baking soda in 2 1/2 cups boiling water for a few hours.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Form into a loaf and place in 9 x 13-inch pan or into bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool slightly and slice for sandwiches, if desired.

title: pat's special pork chops
directions: Coat skillet with olive oil.
Lightly brown pork chops on both sides; remove from pan.
Saute onion, pepper and minced garlic in skillet.
Add additional olive oil if necessary.
Return chops to skillet, spooning onion mixture over pork chops.
Pour tomato sauce over chops.
Fill tomato sauce can 1/2 to 3/4 full of water and pour over chops.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and oregano over mixture.
Gently stir mixture with fork.
Bring to a gentle boil. Lower temperature to simmer and cover.
Cook, covered, on low for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by tablespoon or scoop onto greased (Pam spray) pan on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until light brown. Cool on rack.

title: chicken velveeta
directions: Saute onions, pepper and oleo.
Cook spaghetti in 1 1/2 quarts chicken broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in oven 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: hot mustard
directions: Blend dry ingredients; add liquids.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Yields 2 cups.
Great with sandwiches or beside meat.

title: corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt oleo.
Mix the creamed corn, whole corn and melted oleo.
Add sour cream and corn bread mix.
Stir well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: canned green beans
directions: Cover green beans with white vinegar and water.
Add canning salt to each quart of beans.
Cook until beans change color or as long as you want. Fill each quart of beans with the water they were cooked in.
Seal them.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crispy. Remove bacon.
In drippings, saute onion until soft. Add cabbage and toss.
Add rest of ingredients.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until cabbage is glazed, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Put bacon in and stir.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken in large pot with 4 chicken bouillon cubes.
Add sage and poultry seasoning.
Add chopped onions to broth.
Boil until tender; cut into bite-size pieces.
Place chicken on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook about 12 to 16 ounces of stuffing. Place on top of chicken.
Take 2 cans of cream of chicken soup with 2 cans of broth from pan.
Pour soup over chicken and stuffing layer.
Bake at 350° covered with foil, shiny side down. Bake for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: red dressing
directions: Recipe can be cut in half.
Beat for 15 to 20 minutes at medium speed.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together lemonade concentrate, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Put into shell and cover or edge with whipped cream.
Grate some lemon peel over the top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: simple apple pie
directions: Prepare 2 crust pie as directed on package.
Blend sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into apples until well coated. Pour mixture into pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust, seal, flute and slit top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 30 minutes longer.

title: "best caramel icing"
directions: Remove labels from cans and place the unopened cans in a deep boiler and completely cover them with water. Boil these unopened cans for 3 hours, adding hot water as needed to keep cans covered. Be careful to keep cans covered with water the entire cooking time. After 3 hours, remove cans from boiler and open while hot, being careful not to burn yourself. Ice cake with hot mixture.

title: frozen cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apples in food processor.
Stir in sugar and let stand 1/2 hour.
Fold fruit mixture, nuts
and marshmallows in whipped cream.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan and wrap in foil to freeze.
To serve, unwrap and cut into squares.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place a layer of each ingredient in a bowl in order as listed. Refrigerate overnight.

title: "puttin' on the ritz" cookies
directions: Boil
dates
and
milk until thick and spreadable.
Add nuts. Spread on crackers.
Bake in a 300° oven for 5 minutes, no longer.
Cool
and spread with sour cream frosting.
These go fast at our bazaar!

title: sausage - egg brunch
directions: There are two basic smoking methods - hot smoking, in which the game is exposed to more direct, 120° to 180° temperature and cold smoking, the method most often used for fish.
In cold smoking, smoke is directed to the fish from a separate heat source.
What's needed is a 70° to 90° smoking temperature for up to 36 hours.
The easier of the 2 methods, hot smoking, takes 6 to 8 hours, depending on the smoker and the size and amount of fish or game.
For hot smoking, the heat source needs to be 14 to 21 inches from the smoking racks.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in fruit.
Chill.

title: cold curried apple soup
directions: Whisk curry powder, applesauce, white wine, lemon juice and orange juice together and refrigerate to chill thoroughly.
At serving time, whip the cream and cut the apple into thin slices. Ladle soup into bowls and garnish with whipped cream and apple slices.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix chocolate, sugar and flour.
Add milk, beaten egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring often.
Pour into browned pie shell.
Top with meringue; brown in a 350° oven.
Makes 1 pie.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Use a square dish or mold.
Mix Jell-O and water.
Fold in everything but the sour cream.
Put half the mixture in a mold and let set until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Gently spread on remaining mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake pizza crust; cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing mix and spread on top of pizza crust.
Add vegetable toppings and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Topping suggestions include shredded Cheddar cheese, chopped green onion, chopped broccoli florets, shredded carrots, sliced black olives, bacon bits and jalapeno peppers.

title: my own spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions, celery and peppers in oil for 10 minutes, stirring often. Add garlic and cook 2 more minutes. Add crushed tomatoes, tomato puree, sweet basil, oregano leaves, bay leaf and sugar and add salt to taste. Simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix together thoroughly the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix nuts, cinnamon and powdered sugar together; set aside.
Pour 1/2 batter into lightly greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 the nut mixture over this.
Add remaining batter, then remaining nut mixture on top.
Increase oven temperature to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Invert onto dish. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: cream apple pie
directions: Mix apple pie mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Put mixture in pie crust.
Mix instant vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Spread over pie and refrigerate.

title: mexi-casserole
directions: Arrange tamales in 9 X 13 pan; pour chili on top.
Add onions and olives.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Add cheese and chips on top during the last 15 minutes.

title: shrimp snack
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Separate biscuits into thirds (layers).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Spread with mixture; top with a water chestnut.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 to 30 servings.

title: ham fingers
directions: Grind clear meat and pork steak together.
Mix eggs, milk and cracker crumbs together with hands.
Heat remaining ingredients to pour over ham fingers ad you place in oven.
You can mix this together and form like small sausages or fingers the night before, as it takes a little time to form them.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with instant pudding powder.
(Be sure pudding is instant.)
Add drained fruit cocktail, Mandarin oranges and marshmallows.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, chicken and peas together. Mix 1/2 cheese into rice mixture. Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top, then cover with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken breasts and debone.
Cut into pieces.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all ingredients and cook in crock-pot 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: pickled squash
directions: Slice squash thin.
Chop onions and bell peppers.
Alternate vegetables with salt.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Boil liquids and spices a little.
Add vegetables and just heat.
Spoon into jars and seal.

title: "fanny farmer" fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, counting time from when boiling is reached.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and chocolate chips until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate until hardened.
Cut into squares.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables.
Add soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.
This is really good and easy.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese and condensed milk until fluffy.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and cocoa.
Pour into chocolate pie crust.
Let stand in refrigerator at least
1 hour before serving.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: easy short ribs
directions: Season short ribs.
Let stand for 2 hours or overnight.
In roasting pan, place onions and celery leaves first and place the short ribs on top.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.
Pour fat off. Serve dressed with favorite dressing.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and blend in bananas, milk and vanilla.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a small bowl, combine flour, nuts, soda and salt; mix well.
Add to banana mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Remove.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla; mix.
Blend in flour, then nuts.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Let come to a boil and put in 2 quarts of strawberries.
Let boil 20 minutes.
After coming to a boiling point, seal in hot jars.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar together well.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.

title: moist cornbread
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in boiling water.
Stir until well mixed.
Beat eggs and milk in a small bowl.
Add to cornmeal mixture, stirring until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Pour crushed chips into large baking dish.
Mix first 5 ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is bubbly.

title: rice 'n broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Drain each.
To hot rice, add Cheez Whiz, soup, milk and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak stir-fry
directions: Spray a skillet with cooking oil spray.
Heat 1 minute.
Cook half of the beef until browned, stirring often.
Remove and set aside.
Remove skillet from heat; spray with cooking spray. Repeat with remaining beef.
Remove skillet from heat; spray with cooking spray.
Cook red or green peppers and onion with garlic and crushed red peppers until tender, stirring often.
Stir in gravy.
Heat to boiling.
Return beef to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: donna powell's turkey soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and cook.
Stir in flour.
Add broth, noodles, celery and seasonings.
Cook until tender.
Add corn, milk, pimento and turkey.
Heat, but do not boil.
Delicious and a great way to use leftover turkey.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown sausage and add to melted cheese in crock-pot.
Add scallions and tomatoes.
Simmer until thick.

title: peanut butter log
directions: Use thick pan. Cook on medium heat. Let water, syrup and sugar boil until it turns to thread or hard-ball stage when dropped in cold water. Pour syrup mixture into the beaten egg whites slowly, beating until it starts to get thick. Then spread on waxed paper that you have sprinkled with powdered sugar. Then spread peanut butter on top of this. Using the paper to keep smooth, roll into a log. Chill in fridge until cool, then slice.

title: best angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Fold together cake mix and pineapple until just moistened.
Pour into a 9 x 13 ungreased pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Bake in an ungreased casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut in bite-sized chunks.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mother's easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, evaporated milk and marshmallows in a medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils. Roll and stir 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into 25 pieces.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate chips over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Quickly pour on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Melt the vanilla chips until smooth and add peanut butter; stir until combined.
Pour over the chocolate and swirl.
Let cool or put in refrigerator.
Break into pieces.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, eggs, margarine and vanilla well.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8 depending on serving size.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix seasonings in water.
Mix browned beef, cooked macaroni, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Pour 1/2 mixture in Pyrex dish; add 1/2 of cheese.
Pour remaining meat mixture and top with cheese.
Makes two 8 x 8 or one 8 x 12 inch pyrex dishes.
Freezes well for another meal.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cooking Time: 25 minutes.

title: banana squares
directions: *To sour milk, place 1 teaspoon of white vinegar in a measuring cup; add enough milk to equal 1/4 cup.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook cabbage in 4 tablespoons butter over low heat until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
This will take 35 to 45 minutes.
Prepare noodles according to package directions, using salted water, and then drain well.
Add noodles, remaining 2 tablespoons butter and salt and pepper to cabbage and cook until heated through.

title: braised beef tips over rice
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for one hour or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Place sugar in medium mixing bowl, stir in syrup.
Place in oven and cook on High power for 4 minutes.
Remove and stir in peanuts, vanilla, salt and butter.
Return to oven and cook for another 4 to 5 minutes until light brown, remove.
Stir in baking soda until light and frothy.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet or wax paper and let cool 45 minutes or until hard.
Place in Ziploc bag or airtight container for storage.

title: dinner chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and celery in water, drain. Set aside. Melt butter, add flour and stir well. Add salt and milk. Cook until thick stirring constantly. Add cheese and drained potato mixture. Add tomatoes and parsley.

title: pink delight jello salad
directions: Mix and put in freezer.
Makes enough for 3 Cool Whip containers.

title: bread stuffing
directions: In small saucepan, dissolve the bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add onion and simmer 5 minutes.

title: great grandma's christmas cookies
directions: Stir in 3 1/2 C flour with 1 teaspoon of salt, 1 teaspoon of baking powder.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll 1/8 in. thick on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375 for about 10 minutes. Decorate as desired.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice until it thickens.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheesy bites
directions: Crumble bacon and drain sausage on paper towels.
Cool.
Grate cheese; add to Bisquick along with sausage.
Stir well.
Slowly stir water in with fork.
Make into small balls; brown in 400° oven for 10 or 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 325 to 350 about 20 min.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: can't wait apple cake
directions: Combine apples, oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to batter.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Cake batter will be very thick.)

title: pork ala muse
directions: Slice pork and serve on platter over pasta.
Cover with tomatoes.
Garnish and enjoy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in soup, sauce, paste, and salt.
Cook until mixture begins to boil.
Layer tortilla chips in a 9x13 pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour mixture over the top of chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve with salsa.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients.
Pour over the crackers and pretzels and mix well.
Let set for at least one hour.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the peanut butter. Blend well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill 20 minutes.
Add the melted chocolate by spreading over the peanut butter mixture. Chill an additional 15 minutes and cut.

title: hash-brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns and combine in a large mixing bowl with 1/2 cup butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion, sour cream, cream of mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Blend ingredients well.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Boil vinegar and and sugar for 2 minutes.
Allow to cool. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour vinegar sauce over salad and allow to stand overnight.
Keeps well in a covered container in refrigerator.
Keep on hand for quick meals.

title: sugar-free berried delight
directions: *Or use 1 (6 ounce serving size) package pudding and 2 1/2 cups cold milk.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook vegetables on medium until tender.
Add meat and cook until browned.
Drain.
Stir in ketchup, water, chili powder, salt, black pepper and hot sauce.
Reduce to low for 15 minutes and simmer or until thick.
Serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cheese and crumbs.
Add liquid from asparagus to mushroom soup.
Put layer of cheese-crumbs mixture in bottom of greased casserole, then a layer of asparagus tips.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover with a layer of soup mixture. Repent layers until ingredients are used up, ending with a topping of cheese-crumbs mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices. Layer potatoes and apples in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, salt and cinnamon, sprinkle and dot with butter.
Repeat layers until dish is filled.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place 2 to 3 teaspoons in coffee mug.
Add hot water.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Combine
oleo,	sugar,	flour and nuts.
Press	into
a 9-inch pie pan, going halfway up the sides.
Bake	at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Cut two pieces of foil large enough to wrap the meat in. Sprinkle half of soup mix and mushrooms on foil.
Place roast on foil and sprinkle rest of soup mix and mushrooms on top of meat. Wrap very securely.
Place in oven in flat roaster and bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: fresh strawberry muffins with strawberry cream cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle berries with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs.
Blend with oil, milk and orange rind.
Add to flour mixture and stir.
Drain berries; fold into batter.
Fill paper lined cups and bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Serve with cream cheese.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Serve.

title: sweet 'n sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots seven minutes.
Drain.
Peel and slice onions; separate into rings.
Slice green pepper.
Combine these vegetables in a casserole.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients. Cook for fifteen minutes.
Pour over vegetables. Serve hot or cold.

title: cranberry-apple sauce
directions: In large saucepan, combine cranberries, sugar, cranberry-apple juice cocktail, allspice and ginger; bring to boiling.
Stir in apples and grated orange peel; simmer 2 minutes or until almost all berries have popped.
Pour mixture into bowl; cool.
Cover and refrigerate until cold.
Before serving, stir in chopped orange and pecans.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Combine 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar in bag.
Add biscuits and shake to coat.
Place biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
In saucepan, mix margarine, brown sugar, Eagle Brand milk, 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. Bring to a boil and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: westport cranberry relish
directions: Coarsely grind first 3 ingredients.
Stir in sugar, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Cook raisins and apricots in 1/2 cup water over medium heat until raisins are plump, about 5 to 10 minutes; drain.
Stir raisins, apricots and pecans into relish. Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Yields approximately 3 1/2 cups relish.

title: creamy pineapple-orange jello salad
directions: Use an 8-inch square pan.
Bring pineapple with juice to a boil.
Off heat, stir in jello to dissolve.
Cool.
Stir in buttermilk and fold in Cool Whip until no lumps remain.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pan and refrigerate 4 hours.
Serve in cut squares on lettuce leaves, garnished with canned mandarin orange segments.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In skillet brown meat; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
In a separate bowl prepare muffin mix according to directions, adding 1/2 can of the onions.
Spoon muffin mixture around outer edge of the casserole.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions. Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix beans with 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Put in bottom of a medium serving dish.
Put avocados on top of beans.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and second 1/2 package taco seasoning and layer on top of avocados.
Put grated cheeses on next, then olives, then tomatoes and lastly, onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water in a large warm bowl.
Add warm milk, sugar, salt, margarine and eggs.
Stir in 2-3 cups flour.
Beat vigorously with wooden spoon until smooth (150 strokes).
Gradually stir in another 2-3 cups flour.
Turn out on a floured board, round, and knead for 5-10 minutes.
Cover and let rest for 20 minutes.
Shape into rolls or coffee cakes, place in greased pans.
Brush surface with oil and cover.
Place in refrigerator for 2-24 hours.
When ready to bake, remove from refrigerator and let stand for 10-15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes.

title: stuffed franks
directions: Slit franks lengthwise, not cutting completely through.
In each slit, place 1/3 slice of cheese and 3 dill pickle slices. Wrap in 1/2 to 1 strip of uncooked bacon. Secure with toothpicks. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bacon is done, about 10 minutes.

title: deviled robin eggs
directions: Shell the eggs and slice them in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks and mash them with the mayonnaise and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix until it is smoothly blended and creamy. Stuff equal amounts into the hollow of each egg white.
Sprinkle parsley or fresh herbs on top, if desired.

title: beef-macaroni delight
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening.
Add tomatoes, sauce, steak sauce, green pepper, parsley, soup, salt and pepper.
Simmer at least 20 minutes.
Boil macaroni until tender.
Combine with meat mixture.
Mix lightly.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese and then add Parmesan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Drain, brown meat and onion; drain off excess fat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: best ever chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa, salt and egg yolks together. Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients for 1 minute and bottle.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple-pimento salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice and dissolve jello in juice.
Cut pimentos fine.
Mix and mash well with softened cheese.
Add all ingredients (except cream) together and mix well.
Whip the cream and fold into mixture.
Chill.

title: crazy cake
directions: Line pan with marshmallows.
Mix cake mix as on box, then pour over marshmallows.
Mix cherry pie filling and jello in bowl. Pour over cake mix.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Can substitute any flavor pie filling and jello.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: chicken broth
directions: Boil, then simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and strain.
Use as base for all forms of chicken soup.

title: reuben roll
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg, onions and seasonings.
Blend well.
On a sheet of waxed paper, shape mixture into a 6 x 14-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with sauerkraut and grated cheese, leaving a 1-inch border around all edges.
Starting with narrow end, carefully roll the mixture, jelly-roll fashion, using waxed paper as a guide.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large bowl, put flour and cut in shortening and sugar.
Add yeast, buttermilk and soda.
Mix well.
Cover bowl tightly and put in refrigerator for 2 hours before using.
Take out as much as is needed and roll on floured board or waxed paper and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or maybe a little more.
Dough will keep for several days in refrigerator.

title: gingersnap pie crust
directions: Roll
gingersnaps with rolling pin or processor to make fine crumbs.
There
should
be
1/4 cups of crumbs.
Blend butter and crumbs thoroughly, then pat mixture over bottom and up sides of an 8-inch pie pan into a uniform layer.
Bake in a moderately hot
oven
at
350° for 10 minutes, then cool thoroughly
before filling with precooked or chiffon pie filling. Makes one 8-inch crust.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: apfel chuechli (swiss apple fritters)
directions: Make a dough with flour, water, vinegar, oil, salt and egg yolk.
Beat egg white and add.
Cut apples in circular slices.
Dip them into the dough and fry in deep fat until golden brown.
Remove from deep fryer, and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Serve at once.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Gradually add eggs, bananas, flour, soda, and salt.
Stir in nuts and pour into 4 small greased and floured pans or 2 large pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chiffon rhubarb pie
directions: Mix ingredients; place in pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecued round steak
directions: Cut steak into crosswise slices 1-inch wide. Heat oil; brown steak on all sides. Remove meat and place in casserole dish. Pour off fat, then place garlic, vinegar, sugar, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, salt, dry mustard and pepper in skillet. Simmer 3 minutes. Pour over steak; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients as for any layer cake.
Batter will be thinner than usual.
Put 4 tablespoons of batter into greased and floured cake pan.
Bump pans gently with hands to spread batter over the entire pan. Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Do not cook too long or allow layer to get brown.
Partially cool before removing from pan.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix the cake according to directions on package.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the Ricotta cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla; pour over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Stir just enough to moisten well.
Store in covered jars in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Bake when desired for 18 to 20 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle top generously with granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: quick lowfat beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in soup pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about 15 minutes. Add water, if needed. Makes 4 hearty portions.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, baking powder, cloves and salt.
Stir in margarine, water and molasses until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool slightly on cake rack.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Mix all ingredients together; serve cold.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham and cheese.
Put in baking dish and trench middle of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out and put ham and cheese in middle, then top with tomatoes that are left.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Shape into small balls and flatten down.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until just golden around the edges.

title: quick barbecue sandwiches
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion together.
Add tomato soup, barbecue sauce and mustard.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and mix.
Add raisins.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased pan.
Mix together 1 cup sugar and 2 cups boiling water.
Pour over cake mixture and bake 3 or 4 minutes in moderate oven.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Place the grated cabbage in a bowl.
Add the green pepper, onion, celery and frankfurters.
Mix well and chill.

title: amazing carrot cake(3 layer cake)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together, set aside.
In large bowl beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly beat in oil. Add flour mixture slowly, beating until smooth.
Mix in carrots and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes be fore removing from pans (do this).
Then cool completely on racks.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook meat and onions in 1 tablespoon fat or shortening until lightly browned.
Add other ingredients and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into well greased casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: 7-up party flip
directions: Pour Hawaiian Punch into a pitcher or punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Place a small scoopful of sherbet into each glass.
Slowly pour 7-Up and Hawaiian Punch mixture over sherbet. Makes 2 1/2 quarts or about 16 (6 ounce) servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer egg slices on this.
Blend broth and soup in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour broth and soup mixture over chicken and egg slices; let stand a few minutes before putting on crust (may need to add a little more broth).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet and drain. Add diced zucchini. Cover with pizza sauce and simmer until zucchini is cooked. Slice cheese and place on top of zucchini mixture. Turn off heat. Serve when cheese is melted.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix well. Let rise 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: baked eggs and sausage
directions: Line 9 x 9-inch square pan with slices of bread.
Fry sausage and put on top of bread.
Spread cheese on top.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle salt and pepper and 1/2 teaspoon dried mustard.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: Melt margarine in a large Dutch oven over medium heat; add onion, celery and bay leaf.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk and broth; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.

title: jimmy's fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice firm green tomatoes into quarter or half-inch sliced. Dip each slice in cornmeal to which a dash of sugar and salt have been added.
Fry in oil until brown, turning once during cooking.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° or until potatoes are done.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans with taco seasoning mix and spread bean mixture evenly in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Makes approximately 6 cups.
Serve with nacho chips.
Makes a good party dip.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Place on medium heat, do not boil.
After 5 minutes, turn to low heat and hold for 20 minutes so flavors will blend.
Strain before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix crabmeat, cream cheese and seasonings; cover with slivered almonds.
Chill and serve.
